1
00:00:00,033 --> 00:00:01,775
- Is this the place?
- Yes.

2
00:00:01,775 --> 00:00:04,905
[Bonjour Bakery]

3
00:00:04,905 --> 00:00:08,175
[The First Customers Of The Afternoon]

4
00:00:08,175 --> 00:00:09,910
- We have new customers.
- Really?

5
00:00:12,713 --> 00:00:13,887
Hello.

6
00:00:13,887 --> 00:00:16,183
Hello, welcome.

7
00:00:16,183 --> 00:00:18,285
[Come On In]

8
00:00:18,717 --> 00:00:20,187
Since there are four of you,

9
00:00:20,187 --> 00:00:23,123
why don't you sit over here
at Table Three?

10
00:00:23,123 --> 00:00:24,358
Thank you.

11
00:00:24,358 --> 00:00:26,994
[A Woman Came With Her Daughter And Friends]

12
00:00:26,994 --> 00:00:29,630
- It smells like bread.
- It's nice.

13
00:00:29,630 --> 00:00:30,831
- Chamomile.
- Is it hot?

14
00:00:30,831 --> 00:00:31,832
Yes, you can drink it hot.

15
00:00:31,832 --> 00:00:33,267
- Then-
- It's not coffee.

16
00:00:33,267 --> 00:00:35,072
She wants chamomile?

17
00:00:36,370 --> 00:00:38,205
When I overhear things like that,

18
00:00:38,205 --> 00:00:40,507
- I find myself writing down the order.
- Right?

19
00:00:40,507 --> 00:00:43,210
[The Body Responds First]
It's become second nature.

20
00:00:43,210 --> 00:00:45,736
And I keep looking at the coffee machine.

21
00:00:47,114 --> 00:00:49,783
[The Manager Overhears The Order]

22
00:00:50,250 --> 00:00:52,653
[And Starts Making Lemon Honey Tea]

23
00:00:53,053 --> 00:00:54,555
[During The Training Process]
It doesn't taste artificial.

24
00:00:54,555 --> 00:00:56,557
Right? Because you use real lemon zest,

25
00:00:56,557 --> 00:00:58,492
it tastes extra fresh.

26
00:01:00,427 --> 00:01:02,095
It looks mouth-wateringly good.

27
00:01:02,095 --> 00:01:03,430
[A Lemon Tea Made With Hand-Squeezed Lemons]

28
00:01:03,430 --> 00:01:06,099
- Please add two.
- This was why it tasted so good.

29
00:01:06,099 --> 00:01:08,435
[The Secret Is A Generous Amount
Of Freshly Squeezed Lemon]

30
00:01:08,435 --> 00:01:10,571
It makes your mouth water.

31
00:01:10,571 --> 00:01:11,980
Here you go.

32
00:01:12,973 --> 00:01:15,776
[The Sweet And Sour Lemon Honey Tea
That Stole Hee Ae's Heart]

33
00:01:16,343 --> 00:01:18,378
[Loaded With Fresh Lemon]

34
00:01:18,378 --> 00:01:20,547
[Meanwhile Barista Seon Ho]

35
00:01:23,684 --> 00:01:27,454
[Skillfully Works The Machine With Both Hands]

36
00:01:28,121 --> 00:01:31,325
[Whips Up Two Cups Of Coffee In A Flash]

37
00:01:31,325 --> 00:01:33,126
- "<i>Bokbunja</i> Tart."
- That sounds tasty.

38
00:01:33,126 --> 00:01:35,944
- They also have <i>Bokbunja</i> Madeleines.
- Okay, let's go in.

39
00:01:37,397 --> 00:01:38,398
Hello.

40
00:01:38,398 --> 00:01:40,367
- Hello.
- Hello.

41
00:01:45,906 --> 00:01:47,240
[Waiting For Them To Settle In]
Are you tired?

42
00:01:47,240 --> 00:01:49,109
- Are you okay?
- I'm tired.

43
00:01:49,109 --> 00:01:51,778
- Hello.
- It's a magnifying glass.

44
00:01:51,778 --> 00:01:54,681
Take a look at the menu.
Order everything that looks good.

45
00:01:54,681 --> 00:01:56,383
- Go to town.
- Are you treating me, Mom?

46
00:01:56,383 --> 00:01:58,251
- Yes, I'll treat you.
- Really?

47
00:01:58,251 --> 00:02:00,220
- No, I'll pay.
- I can afford this much.

48
00:02:00,220 --> 00:02:01,388
I'll treat you, Mom.

49
00:02:01,388 --> 00:02:03,557
- All right, then.
- If you're paying, I'm going all out.

50
00:02:03,557 --> 00:02:05,292
- Go ahead.
- Yes!

51
00:02:05,292 --> 00:02:07,107
We have a policy here

52
00:02:07,107 --> 00:02:08,895
- where we have to check your ID.
- Of course.

53
00:02:08,895 --> 00:02:11,398
- Go on, Mom.
- Sure.

54
00:02:11,398 --> 00:02:14,534
[While She Gets Her ID]
Of course, I will comply.

55
00:02:14,534 --> 00:02:16,069
[Another Customer Enters]
Hello.

56
00:02:16,069 --> 00:02:18,005
- Kim Hee Ae.
- Yes.

57
00:02:18,005 --> 00:02:19,806
- I'm a local.
- I see.

58
00:02:19,806 --> 00:02:22,275
- I live just over there.
- Oh, right.

59
00:02:22,275 --> 00:02:23,443
- Hello.
- We met before.

60
00:02:23,443 --> 00:02:25,245
Yes, why don't you take a seat?

61
00:02:25,245 --> 00:02:28,248
[Who Is This Man That Met Seon Ho Before?]

62
00:02:29,950 --> 00:02:31,018
Hello.

63
00:02:31,018 --> 00:02:33,687
[It's Mr. Gi Ho Jik Seon Ho Met Him On His Way Into Work]

64
00:02:33,687 --> 00:02:36,556
Come and visit our café. We're open now.

65
00:02:36,556 --> 00:02:38,623
Are you Seon Ho?

66
00:02:40,060 --> 00:02:41,228
[He Recognized Seon Ho]
We just opened.

67
00:02:41,228 --> 00:02:44,197
[And Greeted Him Warmly]
Drop by if you get the chance.

68
00:02:44,197 --> 00:02:46,900
[He Came By As Promised]
Use this towel to wipe your hands.

69
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:48,502
We can just take it to go, right?

70
00:02:48,502 --> 00:02:50,237
Yes, we can pack them up for you,

71
00:02:50,237 --> 00:02:53,669
but not the cream-filled ones,
just the baked goods and bread.

72
00:02:54,775 --> 00:02:58,945
[While Mr. Gi Ho Jik Chooses What To Buy]

73
00:02:59,713 --> 00:03:01,782
I got to come here thanks to you.

74
00:03:03,116 --> 00:03:04,951
You get to benefit from me.

75
00:03:04,951 --> 00:03:06,853
I'm good for something.

76
00:03:06,853 --> 00:03:09,456
[The Hall Team Is Suddenly Very Busy]

77
00:03:13,136 --> 00:03:14,494
What else do you want?

78
00:03:14,494 --> 00:03:15,629
- Pick one more.
- One more?

79
00:03:15,629 --> 00:03:19,522
- This one or this one?
- The tart.

80
00:03:20,467 --> 00:03:22,269
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

81
00:03:22,269 --> 00:03:23,927
This is the brioche.

82
00:03:23,927 --> 00:03:26,488
[Dessert Is Served]
This is the Strawberry Tart.

83
00:03:28,208 --> 00:03:30,510
This is the financier.

84
00:03:30,510 --> 00:03:33,693
The Crème Brûlée is being torched,
so I'll bring it over a little later.

85
00:03:36,083 --> 00:03:38,552
Should I do the torching?

86
00:03:38,552 --> 00:03:40,921
- Yes, you do it.
- Okay.

87
00:03:40,921 --> 00:03:43,190
- Don't make me do it.
- Okay.

88
00:03:43,957 --> 00:03:47,694
[What A Laugh]

89
00:03:48,095 --> 00:03:49,996
Here is the brûlée.

90
00:03:49,996 --> 00:03:53,366
Tap the top twice with a spoon to crack it,

91
00:03:53,366 --> 00:03:55,302
- then mix it in before eating.
- Okay.

92
00:03:55,302 --> 00:03:56,703
- Enjoy.
- Okay.

93
00:03:56,703 --> 00:03:58,362
- Thank you.
- Sure.

94
00:03:59,406 --> 00:04:01,032
Let's tap it together.

95
00:04:01,875 --> 00:04:03,498
Try this.

96
00:04:04,177 --> 00:04:06,079
- Try it.
- It's good.

97
00:04:06,079 --> 00:04:07,380
It's tasty.

98
00:04:07,380 --> 00:04:11,010
- I need to take a photo of this.
- Go ahead.

99
00:04:11,010 --> 00:04:14,054
How can I get the best shot?

100
00:04:14,054 --> 00:04:15,422
[Green Barley Field Tart, Blueberry Éclair]

101
00:04:15,422 --> 00:04:19,493
[Taking A Picture As Soon As It's Served]

102
00:04:19,493 --> 00:04:22,028
Enough of that. Now, cut it.

103
00:04:22,028 --> 00:04:23,630
Cut it so we can eat it.

104
00:04:23,630 --> 00:04:26,266
It's too pretty to cut.

105
00:04:26,266 --> 00:04:28,502
How do I cut this?

106
00:04:28,502 --> 00:04:30,488
Just cut it down the middle.

107
00:04:31,705 --> 00:04:34,174
I just feel bad because it's so pretty.

108
00:04:34,174 --> 00:04:36,409
Goodness.

109
00:04:36,409 --> 00:04:38,979
- It was made with so much thought.
- Seriously.

110
00:04:38,979 --> 00:04:40,714
This part is the green barley.

111
00:04:40,714 --> 00:04:44,117
- Yes, I saw it on the card.
- It's mixed with things like citron.

112
00:04:44,117 --> 00:04:46,386
Just cut straight through it.

113
00:04:46,386 --> 00:04:47,587
There's no other way.

114
00:04:47,587 --> 00:04:50,023
- You just have to do it.
- It's the only way.

115
00:04:50,023 --> 00:04:51,925
[No Choice But To Cut It]
Just go straight in.

116
00:04:51,925 --> 00:04:53,997
Let's give it a taste.

117
00:04:56,630 --> 00:04:58,465
- Can you smell the barley?
- Yes.

118
00:04:58,465 --> 00:05:02,068
[Mom Takes A Big Bite First]

119
00:05:02,068 --> 00:05:03,511
It's good.

120
00:05:04,971 --> 00:05:07,823
- It's not too sweet.
- Good.

121
00:05:11,444 --> 00:05:13,113
Is it all right?

122
00:05:13,113 --> 00:05:15,313
- It's good.
- It's delicious.

123
00:05:16,917 --> 00:05:18,632
You need to be ruthless.

124
00:05:19,352 --> 00:05:20,854
Just cut it up like this.

125
00:05:20,854 --> 00:05:23,623
Can you cut the rest, Mom?

126
00:05:24,357 --> 00:05:27,894
[She's Still Mom's Little Girl]

127
00:05:28,461 --> 00:05:29,729
Can I have the rest of this?

128
00:05:29,729 --> 00:05:31,898
[Of Course, Not]

129
00:05:31,898 --> 00:05:37,270
I've seen tarts in other bakeries.

130
00:05:37,270 --> 00:05:41,174
- But this éclair is new to me.
- Same.

131
00:05:41,174 --> 00:05:44,244
They used huge blueberries.

132
00:05:44,244 --> 00:05:46,313
That's what this region is famous for.

133
00:05:46,313 --> 00:05:49,049
It would look bad to use small ones.

134
00:05:49,049 --> 00:05:51,667
- Exactly.
- Gochang's pride is on the line.

135
00:05:53,553 --> 00:05:56,122
[Gochang's Blueberries
Are Extra Big And Extra Juicy]

136
00:05:56,122 --> 00:05:59,192
[They Live Up To Gochang's Reputation]

137
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:02,662
[How Does It Taste?]
Is it good?

138
00:06:06,099 --> 00:06:07,500
I cut it too big.

139
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:09,936
[Nod Of Approval]
Is it good?

140
00:06:10,737 --> 00:06:11,811
It's not too sweet.

141
00:06:11,811 --> 00:06:13,506
[The Highest Compliment Moms Can Offer]

142
00:06:13,506 --> 00:06:14,841
And it's got...

143
00:06:14,841 --> 00:06:16,443
It's got a kind of sour kick.

144
00:06:16,443 --> 00:06:17,844
What is that zesty flavor?

145
00:06:17,844 --> 00:06:19,980
Is it the blueberries?

146
00:06:19,980 --> 00:06:21,160
What is that?

147
00:06:22,549 --> 00:06:24,818
[It's The Coulis Filling]

148
00:06:26,553 --> 00:06:29,289
[A French Purée Made By Blending
Gochang's Blueberries]

149
00:06:29,289 --> 00:06:31,691
[Smooth Like Jam
With A Deep And Rich Flavor]

150
00:06:33,059 --> 00:06:34,461
[Blueberry Coulis]

151
00:06:34,461 --> 00:06:36,696
[The Customer Guessed Right Like A Pro]

152
00:06:36,696 --> 00:06:38,498
What would you like to order, sir?

153
00:06:38,498 --> 00:06:40,233
- You're buying to go, right?
- Yes.

154
00:06:40,233 --> 00:06:42,636
Three of these, and three of those.

155
00:06:42,636 --> 00:06:43,837
[3 <i>Bokbunja</i> Madeleines
3 Citrus Madeleines]

156
00:06:43,837 --> 00:06:45,305
[3 Bonjour Financiers]
And three of these.

157
00:06:45,305 --> 00:06:47,540
- Give me four of each.
- You want four?

158
00:06:47,540 --> 00:06:50,210
All right. I'll be back in a flash.

159
00:06:50,944 --> 00:06:53,613
You really came as I asked you to.

160
00:06:53,613 --> 00:06:54,681
- What?
- Yesterday, I mean.

161
00:06:54,681 --> 00:06:57,851
I thought I'd get in trouble if I didn't.

162
00:07:00,520 --> 00:07:01,755
Thank you for keeping your promise.

163
00:07:01,755 --> 00:07:03,857
I didn't want to get a scolding.

164
00:07:03,857 --> 00:07:05,938
A scolding from me? I couldn't dare.

165
00:07:10,163 --> 00:07:12,966
Who are you sharing all these with?

166
00:07:12,966 --> 00:07:14,034
My wife likes them.

167
00:07:14,034 --> 00:07:15,902
Is that right?

168
00:07:18,038 --> 00:07:21,508
[Simple But Hearfelt Baked Goods
Like The Senior Who Ordered Them]

169
00:07:23,310 --> 00:07:26,980
[Seon Ho Wraps Them Up In A Pretty Package]

170
00:07:37,223 --> 00:07:39,059
Let's go. Is it right next door?

171
00:07:39,059 --> 00:07:40,527
Don't trouble yourself.

172
00:07:40,527 --> 00:07:43,630
It's okay. I'll walk with you.

173
00:07:43,630 --> 00:07:45,966
How can I repay my gratitude?

174
00:07:45,966 --> 00:07:47,000
For what?

175
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:49,135
[Seon Ho Is Grateful]
For coming to our café.

176
00:07:49,135 --> 00:07:51,638
[That The Elderly Kept His Promise]
I live right next door. How could I not?

177
00:07:51,638 --> 00:07:53,707
- Where is your house?
- It's right here.

178
00:07:53,707 --> 00:07:56,009
- Oh, you live here?
- Yes.

179
00:07:56,009 --> 00:07:58,578
You live in such a nice place.

180
00:07:58,578 --> 00:08:01,147
- Are you the richest man in Gochang?
- Rich?

181
00:08:01,147 --> 00:08:03,049
I live with my son,
so I guess that makes me rich.

182
00:08:03,049 --> 00:08:04,733
- Thank you.
- Bye.

183
00:08:10,890 --> 00:08:13,293
- My wife is in the hospital.
- I see.

184
00:08:14,094 --> 00:08:17,597
- Are you heading to the hospital now?
- Yes.

185
00:08:17,597 --> 00:08:19,349
I got her these treats to distract her.

186
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:23,008
- Drive safely.
- I will do.

187
00:08:24,738 --> 00:08:28,675
[He Heads Off To The Hospital
With Pastries For His Wife]

188
00:08:31,378 --> 00:08:32,846
It's tasty.

189
00:08:32,846 --> 00:08:34,535
Is it?

190
00:08:37,751 --> 00:08:40,720
[Pastries Filled With Love Successfully Delivered]

191
00:08:41,354 --> 00:08:44,257
[3:40 p.m.]

192
00:08:48,228 --> 00:08:50,430
[Another Customer Spotted]

193
00:08:51,031 --> 00:08:53,767
[Seon Ho Goes To Greet Them]

194
00:08:54,267 --> 00:08:56,169
- Hello.
- Hello.

195
00:08:56,169 --> 00:08:57,737
- Hello, come on in.
- Hello.

196
00:08:57,737 --> 00:08:59,272
- How many people?
- Four.

197
00:08:59,272 --> 00:09:02,142
[The Compulsory ID Check]
Can I check your ID? It's a regulation.

198
00:09:02,142 --> 00:09:03,943
I only need to see one

199
00:09:03,943 --> 00:09:06,800
- to make sure one of you is over 65.
- Okay.

200
00:09:09,382 --> 00:09:10,617
[He Passed The ID Check]
That's great.

201
00:09:10,617 --> 00:09:12,285
Come this way.

202
00:09:13,586 --> 00:09:15,523
- This is your table.
- Okay.

203
00:09:18,158 --> 00:09:20,293
This is so nice.

204
00:09:20,293 --> 00:09:22,595
It's so pretty here.

205
00:09:22,595 --> 00:09:24,397
It's not easy for us

206
00:09:24,397 --> 00:09:26,699
- to get together for coffee.
- No, it's not.

207
00:09:26,699 --> 00:09:29,636
The first, third, fifth,
and seventh siblings together.

208
00:09:29,636 --> 00:09:34,374
We might have drinks together,
but we never meet up outdoors like this.

209
00:09:34,374 --> 00:09:36,776
[A Family Of 9 Siblings]
It's so nice.

210
00:09:36,776 --> 00:09:38,896
[Enjoying Their First Cafe Outing]
This is really nice.

211
00:09:39,512 --> 00:09:41,014
[Another Family Of Customers]
What a pretty café.

212
00:09:41,014 --> 00:09:43,383
- I thought it was that place.
- Over there?

213
00:09:43,383 --> 00:09:44,984
The flowers are so pretty.

214
00:09:46,820 --> 00:09:48,254
Hello.

215
00:09:48,254 --> 00:09:49,622
Hello.

216
00:09:49,622 --> 00:09:50,523
- Hello.
- Table for three?

217
00:09:50,523 --> 00:09:52,292
- Hello, is it three of you?
- Yes.

218
00:09:52,292 --> 00:09:53,793
In that case...

219
00:09:53,793 --> 00:09:55,862
[Start Them At A Table For Two]
Sit here. I'll bring you another chair.

220
00:09:55,862 --> 00:09:56,996
Thank you.

221
00:09:56,996 --> 00:09:58,562
Mom, sit here.

222
00:10:01,568 --> 00:10:02,735
Here you go.

223
00:10:02,735 --> 00:10:04,904
- Thank you.
- No problem.

224
00:10:04,904 --> 00:10:08,108
[Intently Looking Around]

225
00:10:08,108 --> 00:10:09,442
The flowers are so pretty.

226
00:10:09,442 --> 00:10:10,877
Do you think so, Mom?

227
00:10:10,877 --> 00:10:13,379
How do you feel, Mom?

228
00:10:13,379 --> 00:10:17,150
You got out of school early today.

229
00:10:17,150 --> 00:10:19,152
- I'm happy.
- You are?

230
00:10:19,152 --> 00:10:21,187
Who brought you here?

231
00:10:21,187 --> 00:10:24,023
- Who do you have to thank?
- This one here.

232
00:10:24,023 --> 00:10:25,325
Gyu Seong?

233
00:10:25,325 --> 00:10:26,693
[Firmly Clasping Her Grandson's Hand]

234
00:10:26,693 --> 00:10:28,361
- Gyu Seong.
- Yes?

235
00:10:28,361 --> 00:10:30,497
He is such a handsome guy.

236
00:10:30,497 --> 00:10:31,564
He's handsome?

237
00:10:31,564 --> 00:10:33,199
[He's The Most Handsome Guy In Grandma's Eyes]

238
00:10:33,199 --> 00:10:35,602
[The Nagging Begins]
Are you single or married?

239
00:10:35,602 --> 00:10:36,936
What are you on about, Mom?

240
00:10:36,936 --> 00:10:39,239
- He isn't married yet.
- Not yet.

241
00:10:39,239 --> 00:10:41,107
That's why I asked!

242
00:10:41,107 --> 00:10:44,577
Heaven could call me any day now.

243
00:10:44,577 --> 00:10:46,813
I want to see my great-grandchildren.

244
00:10:46,813 --> 00:10:47,780
- Well...
- Stop it, Mom.

245
00:10:47,780 --> 00:10:49,442
[Please Stop, Grandma]

246
00:10:49,442 --> 00:10:52,218
Since we're serving bread,
use this wet towel to wipe your hands.

247
00:10:52,218 --> 00:10:54,487
The drinks menu is in the front,
and the desserts are in the back.

248
00:10:54,487 --> 00:10:57,290
- Let me know when you're ready.
- Okay, thank you.

249
00:10:59,492 --> 00:11:03,630
[Under The Warm Spring Sun]

250
00:11:03,630 --> 00:11:08,334
[The Honey Bees Are Hard At Work]

251
00:11:09,135 --> 00:11:12,038
[Bonjour Bakery's Honey Bees Are Also Busy]

252
00:11:12,038 --> 00:11:14,374
[Locked In A Struggle With The Flowers]

253
00:11:14,374 --> 00:11:17,477
[It's Honey Bee Cha]
Wait a minute. I can do this.

254
00:11:17,477 --> 00:11:19,045
This is another hard one.

255
00:11:19,045 --> 00:11:20,280
It's tricky.

256
00:11:20,280 --> 00:11:21,640
[The Challenging Dessert Of Day 2]

257
00:11:23,216 --> 00:11:25,718
[Located On The Outskirts
Of Seonunsa Temple In Gochang]

258
00:11:27,020 --> 00:11:31,691
[A Camellia Garden
That Inspired This Dessert]

259
00:11:32,358 --> 00:11:35,762
[Bonjour Camellia Tart]

260
00:11:35,762 --> 00:11:37,797
Oh, the Camellia Tart?

261
00:11:37,797 --> 00:11:40,366
It's very elegant.

262
00:11:40,366 --> 00:11:43,002
[Chef Cha's Favorite Dessert]
I see you had the Camellia Tart.

263
00:11:43,002 --> 00:11:44,270
- How was it? Was it okay?
- Yes.

264
00:11:44,270 --> 00:11:46,339
It was tasty and not too sweet.

265
00:11:46,339 --> 00:11:48,741
If you're drawn to pretty things,

266
00:11:48,741 --> 00:11:50,677
[Proudly Showing Off]
I recommend the Camellia Tart.

267
00:11:50,677 --> 00:11:53,012
[Chef Cha's Most Ambitious Work]
It's the hardest to make.

268
00:11:53,012 --> 00:11:55,181
- For various reasons...
- It was so interesting.

269
00:11:55,181 --> 00:11:58,084
[Chef Cha's Beloved Dessert]

270
00:11:58,084 --> 00:12:00,453
[Our Camellia Tart]

271
00:12:02,855 --> 00:12:06,292
[Fill The Tart Shell With Guava Cream First]

272
00:12:06,292 --> 00:12:09,295
[Top It With Yogurt Whipped Cream]

273
00:12:09,729 --> 00:12:13,032
[Layer The Smooth And Tangy
Yogurt Whipped Cream]

274
00:12:14,234 --> 00:12:17,570
[Then Level It Off]

275
00:12:17,570 --> 00:12:20,173
Did you use tongs to handle the tomatoes?

276
00:12:20,173 --> 00:12:22,675
- What?
- Never mind.

277
00:12:23,543 --> 00:12:24,978
What did you say?

278
00:12:25,378 --> 00:12:27,914
When you picked up the tomatoes earlier,

279
00:12:27,914 --> 00:12:30,750
I couldn't remember
if you used tongs or your hands.

280
00:12:32,719 --> 00:12:35,088
[Laughs In Disbelief]

281
00:12:35,622 --> 00:12:37,423
[What A Silly Question]
You keep making me angry.

282
00:12:37,423 --> 00:12:39,525
Are you going to keep poking the bear?

283
00:12:39,525 --> 00:12:42,629
Go home if you're tired.

284
00:12:42,629 --> 00:12:44,130
- I'm not tired at all.
- Tell this guy

285
00:12:44,130 --> 00:12:46,899
to come in to work later from now on!

286
00:12:46,899 --> 00:12:48,968
[Half-Asleep]
He's worn out from coming in early.

287
00:12:48,968 --> 00:12:51,604
No, I'm really okay.

288
00:12:51,604 --> 00:12:53,273
Unbelievable.

289
00:12:54,941 --> 00:12:57,744
[Brows Furrowed In Concentration]

290
00:12:57,744 --> 00:13:00,813
[Ki Taek, Wake Up And Focus]

291
00:13:02,215 --> 00:13:04,484
[Pick Up The Tomatoes Like This
With Your Fingers]

292
00:13:05,385 --> 00:13:09,622
[Stay Focused Down To Your Fingertips]

293
00:13:09,622 --> 00:13:11,758
[Yes, Chef!]

294
00:13:12,525 --> 00:13:16,596
[This Next Part Is Really Delicate Work]

295
00:13:18,231 --> 00:13:21,834
[Yogurt Whipped Cream]

296
00:13:23,503 --> 00:13:25,471
[Space It Out Evenly]

297
00:13:25,471 --> 00:13:29,142
[And Pipe It On Like Embroidery]

298
00:13:39,218 --> 00:13:42,822
[Guava Cream]

299
00:13:48,594 --> 00:13:53,366
[Enrich The Flavor With Ricotta Cheese]

300
00:13:55,902 --> 00:13:58,571
[And The Key Secret To The Camellia Tart]

301
00:13:59,403 --> 00:14:03,409
[Camellia Flowers Made Of Candied Tomatoes]

302
00:14:06,045 --> 00:14:10,316
[The Camellias Bloom
At The Touch Of Chef Cha's Skilled Fingers]

303
00:14:11,451 --> 00:14:15,688
[Yellow Lemon Cream Stamen]

304
00:14:17,557 --> 00:14:20,360
[And Leaves Made Of Basil]

305
00:14:31,170 --> 00:14:34,507
[The First Sign That Spring Is Coming
After A Cold Winter]

306
00:14:35,708 --> 00:14:38,978
[Bright Red Camellias
Have Bloomed On A Plate]

307
00:14:38,978 --> 00:14:40,546
Bonjour Camellia Turtle.

308
00:14:40,546 --> 00:14:41,881
Tart.

309
00:14:41,881 --> 00:14:43,015
Is that right?

310
00:14:43,015 --> 00:14:45,318
Bonjour Camellia Tart.

311
00:14:45,318 --> 00:14:47,153
Bonjour Camellia Tart!

312
00:14:47,153 --> 00:14:48,821
Can't I stop now?

313
00:14:48,821 --> 00:14:50,723
Bonjour Camellia Tart.

314
00:14:50,723 --> 00:14:51,991
How many times must I say it?

315
00:14:51,991 --> 00:14:53,459
Bonjour Camellia Tart!

316
00:14:53,459 --> 00:14:55,294
Okay, that was good.

317
00:14:57,530 --> 00:15:00,466
- Here's your Camellia Tart and Éclair.
- It's so good.

318
00:15:00,466 --> 00:15:01,968
It's such a pretty color.

319
00:15:01,968 --> 00:15:02,869
It's pretty isn't it?

320
00:15:02,869 --> 00:15:04,537
It's freshly baked, so it'll be extra good.

321
00:15:04,537 --> 00:15:06,028
My goodness.

322
00:15:06,773 --> 00:15:08,841
- It looks like a real flower.
- How can we eat this?

323
00:15:08,841 --> 00:15:11,511
- What are these?
- They're tomatoes.

324
00:15:11,511 --> 00:15:12,779
These are also tomatoes,

325
00:15:12,779 --> 00:15:15,748
- but they've been dried.
- So they are.

326
00:15:15,748 --> 00:15:19,952
It will be extra tasty
since it's freshly baked.

327
00:15:19,952 --> 00:15:23,322
[Let's Start With The Candied Tomatoes]

328
00:15:24,524 --> 00:15:26,893
[Savoring]

329
00:15:26,893 --> 00:15:28,028
It tastes like a gummy.

330
00:15:28,028 --> 00:15:29,712
- Is it good?
- Yes.

331
00:15:30,463 --> 00:15:31,931
Is it the best?

332
00:15:31,931 --> 00:15:33,266
It's very chewy.

333
00:15:33,266 --> 00:15:35,001
- It really is.
- Right?

334
00:15:35,001 --> 00:15:36,736
[Chewy Candied Tomato Camellias]

335
00:15:36,736 --> 00:15:40,039
[Now Let's Try The Marinated Tomatoes]

336
00:15:42,275 --> 00:15:44,528
It's so soft.

337
00:15:46,579 --> 00:15:48,848
- It's such a new flavor.
- Tell me about it.

338
00:15:48,848 --> 00:15:49,849
- But it's so tasty.
- Yeah.

339
00:15:49,849 --> 00:15:51,150
[The Camellias Make Their Smiles Bloom]

340
00:15:51,150 --> 00:15:52,718
Who had it?

341
00:15:52,718 --> 00:15:55,221
The Camellia Tart?
The people on the far right.

342
00:15:55,221 --> 00:15:57,790
The mother and daughter at the far end.

343
00:16:02,462 --> 00:16:05,237
[Curious]

344
00:16:05,237 --> 00:16:07,166
They loved it.

345
00:16:07,166 --> 00:16:08,601
By the way,

346
00:16:08,601 --> 00:16:10,703
- it's so pretty.
- Really?

347
00:16:10,703 --> 00:16:12,125
That's good to hear.

348
00:16:14,106 --> 00:16:16,442
- Hello.
- It's an Éclair.

349
00:16:16,442 --> 00:16:17,577
- Hello.
- Hello.

350
00:16:17,577 --> 00:16:18,911
- Hello, how is it?
- Hello.

351
00:16:18,911 --> 00:16:20,947
- Does it taste okay?
- Hi, it's so good.

352
00:16:20,947 --> 00:16:24,283
- I made these.
- They're delicious and not too sweet.

353
00:16:24,283 --> 00:16:25,852
- Really?
- Yes.

354
00:16:25,852 --> 00:16:28,488
- We're bread lovers.
- Is that right?

355
00:16:28,488 --> 00:16:30,823
What did you think of this Camellia Tart?

356
00:16:30,823 --> 00:16:32,492
Did it live up to your expectations?

357
00:16:32,492 --> 00:16:35,161
- Honestly-
- We've never tried anything like it.

358
00:16:35,161 --> 00:16:36,262
- That's right.
- Really?

359
00:16:36,262 --> 00:16:37,363
But it's so tasty.

360
00:16:37,363 --> 00:16:38,631
- It's delicious.
- I'm so glad.

361
00:16:38,631 --> 00:16:40,800
[A Squeak Of Delight]
It's like a high-end hotel dessert.

362
00:16:40,800 --> 00:16:42,768
- Both this and the Blueberry Éclair?
- All of it.

363
00:16:42,768 --> 00:16:44,837
I think we chose really well.

364
00:16:44,837 --> 00:16:47,607
Thank you so much.

365
00:16:47,607 --> 00:16:48,941
I want to come again.

366
00:16:48,941 --> 00:16:50,498
They're staying open, right?

367
00:16:51,245 --> 00:16:53,246
[100 Percent Eager To Return]
They were really tasty.

368
00:16:53,246 --> 00:16:55,014
They were delicious.

369
00:16:55,014 --> 00:16:58,150
- She moved here-
- I moved from Incheon three years ago.

370
00:16:58,150 --> 00:17:00,720
- I came here with my husband.
- She left to come here.

371
00:17:00,720 --> 00:17:03,256
because this is his hometown.

372
00:17:04,557 --> 00:17:08,094
- Now...
- I'm a little sad about it.

373
00:17:08,094 --> 00:17:10,096
We used to live in the same place.

374
00:17:10,096 --> 00:17:12,098
When she lived close by,

375
00:17:12,098 --> 00:17:14,734
we used to check out
a lot of must-eat places.

376
00:17:14,734 --> 00:17:19,238
I happened to come here yesterday,
so it was lucky timing.

377
00:17:19,238 --> 00:17:22,575
- I'm tearing up.
- I just came to visit her.

378
00:17:22,575 --> 00:17:28,314
She used to live right next door,
and then she left.

379
00:17:28,314 --> 00:17:30,514
[Missing Her Daughter Dearly]
It was a little sad for me.

380
00:17:31,050 --> 00:17:32,285
Hey!

381
00:17:32,285 --> 00:17:35,488
[She Can't Contain Her Happiness
Over Being Reunited]

382
00:17:35,488 --> 00:17:37,491
I'm too full.

383
00:17:38,824 --> 00:17:40,760
- Live a long life.
- A long life?

384
00:17:40,760 --> 00:17:42,428
- So I can treat you.
- Of course.

385
00:17:42,428 --> 00:17:44,730
Let me enjoy a little special treatment.

386
00:17:47,833 --> 00:17:52,171
[We Are Lifelong Besties]

387
00:18:01,013 --> 00:18:03,249
- Are you making the latte?
- Yes.

388
00:18:03,249 --> 00:18:05,885
[Latte Art Made With Painstaking Care]

389
00:18:06,385 --> 00:18:08,254
[A Successful Heart]

390
00:18:08,254 --> 00:18:09,922
What do you think of my heart design?

391
00:18:09,922 --> 00:18:11,657
[Approved]

392
00:18:12,124 --> 00:18:13,526
[Serving The Approved Latte]
Here is the café latte

393
00:18:13,526 --> 00:18:16,762
- and the iced Americano.
- The Americano is for me.

394
00:18:16,762 --> 00:18:19,899
You get it all sketched.

395
00:18:19,899 --> 00:18:20,968
[Slurp]

396
00:18:20,968 --> 00:18:24,337
That's how it's done.
You can't do it yourself.

397
00:18:24,337 --> 00:18:26,672
- It's the same with clothes-
- I can't believe you.

398
00:18:26,672 --> 00:18:29,675
- What?
- The eldest hasn't got his drink yet.

399
00:18:29,675 --> 00:18:32,678
- We've always followed the rules.
- That's right.

400
00:18:32,678 --> 00:18:33,746
But you already took a sip.

401
00:18:33,746 --> 00:18:36,248
[The Eldest Just Finds This Funny]

402
00:18:36,248 --> 00:18:38,250
- Not like back in my day...
- Your day?

403
00:18:38,250 --> 00:18:41,053
[The Third Sibling
Takes A Hit From The Seventh]

404
00:18:41,053 --> 00:18:42,455
Here you go.

405
00:18:42,455 --> 00:18:44,123
I thought they would be bigger.

406
00:18:44,123 --> 00:18:45,124
That's mine.

407
00:18:45,124 --> 00:18:47,693
- This is the Green Barley Brioche.
- Okay.

408
00:18:47,693 --> 00:18:50,096
- Turn your head this way.
- Go ahead.

409
00:18:50,096 --> 00:18:52,031
- Like this?
- Look over there.

410
00:18:52,031 --> 00:18:53,599
Look that way.

411
00:18:53,599 --> 00:18:55,341
I'm not in the frame.

412
00:18:56,936 --> 00:18:58,971
[A Snapshot Of Their First Outing Together]

413
00:18:58,971 --> 00:19:00,706
A silent snapshot.

414
00:19:00,706 --> 00:19:02,041
[Scraping Away]

415
00:19:02,041 --> 00:19:03,577
Thank you.

416
00:19:04,744 --> 00:19:05,779
[One Big Bite]

417
00:19:05,779 --> 00:19:08,114
The eldest should eat first.

418
00:19:08,114 --> 00:19:09,515
You did it again!

419
00:19:09,515 --> 00:19:11,851
- You ate it before he did.
- Did I?

420
00:19:11,851 --> 00:19:14,587
She's a dutiful younger sister.

421
00:19:14,587 --> 00:19:16,822
- Have you not taken a bite?
- No.

422
00:19:16,822 --> 00:19:18,524
What was the name of this dessert?

423
00:19:18,524 --> 00:19:19,825
- Bonjour...
- Bonjour...

424
00:19:19,825 --> 00:19:21,160
Finacio.

425
00:19:21,160 --> 00:19:23,029
[It's Not Bonjour Finacio]

426
00:19:23,029 --> 00:19:25,464
[It's Bonjour Financier]

427
00:19:25,464 --> 00:19:28,534
[Crispy Outside]

428
00:19:28,534 --> 00:19:31,570
[Soft Inside]

429
00:19:33,506 --> 00:19:36,308
[Buttery Richness In Every Bite]

430
00:19:36,308 --> 00:19:38,177
Finangrier.

431
00:19:38,177 --> 00:19:39,825
[Bonjour Financier]

432
00:19:39,825 --> 00:19:42,327
- Did I get it right?
- Yes, you did great.

433
00:19:44,050 --> 00:19:46,285
- My hand is acting up.
- It's acting up?

434
00:19:46,285 --> 00:19:48,387
It's waiting to receive the guest fee.

435
00:19:50,022 --> 00:19:52,358
They probably ground it up.

436
00:19:55,661 --> 00:19:57,517
Try a bite of mine as well.

437
00:19:58,464 --> 00:20:01,667
That's tasty. Great choice.
You chose well.

438
00:20:01,667 --> 00:20:04,070
- The outside is really sweet.
- Really?

439
00:20:04,070 --> 00:20:05,304
[Now The Green Barley Brioche]
This crust...

440
00:20:05,304 --> 00:20:07,406
Look at the green barley inside.

441
00:20:07,406 --> 00:20:09,308
You can smell the barley.

442
00:20:09,308 --> 00:20:10,876
- Give it a taste.
- Okay.

443
00:20:10,876 --> 00:20:13,379
[The Eldest Gets The First Taste]

444
00:20:13,379 --> 00:20:15,781
What a fun dessert.

445
00:20:17,216 --> 00:20:18,551
You can smell the barley.

446
00:20:18,551 --> 00:20:21,887
[The Younger Siblings Also Try A Taste]

447
00:20:21,887 --> 00:20:23,289
- It's delicious.
- This is the best.

448
00:20:23,289 --> 00:20:24,590
It smells really good, too.

449
00:20:24,590 --> 00:20:26,792
It tastes a bit like matcha.

450
00:20:26,792 --> 00:20:27,860
The world is so different now.

451
00:20:27,860 --> 00:20:29,762
Barley used to be food for the poor.

452
00:20:29,762 --> 00:20:32,531
Now, it's served in fancy places like this.

453
00:20:32,531 --> 00:20:34,400
- It's a changed world.
- It is.

454
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:36,037
Who would have thought?

455
00:20:37,837 --> 00:20:41,207
[Green Barley Is Served In All Forms
At Bonjour Bakery]

456
00:20:41,207 --> 00:20:42,274
[2 Brioche, 2 Tarts, 2 Lattes, 1 Honey Lemon Tea]

457
00:20:42,274 --> 00:20:44,744
- I'm sorry the table is so small.
- It's okay.

458
00:20:44,744 --> 00:20:46,145
Thank you for understanding.

459
00:20:46,145 --> 00:20:47,185
Look at that!

460
00:20:47,185 --> 00:20:49,882
Should we take a photo
with our hands in as a memento?

461
00:20:49,882 --> 00:20:52,184
- Grandma, put your hand out.
- Mom.

462
00:20:52,184 --> 00:20:53,085
Just our hands.

463
00:20:53,085 --> 00:20:54,253
- Not like that.
- Hold the fork.

464
00:20:54,253 --> 00:20:55,921
Pick up the fork.

465
00:20:55,921 --> 00:20:57,284
Just our hands.

466
00:20:58,190 --> 00:20:59,525
[Grandson 29 Years Old
Grandma Born In 1929]

467
00:20:59,525 --> 00:21:00,559
One, two...

468
00:21:00,559 --> 00:21:01,994
[Two Generations In One Snapshot]

469
00:21:01,994 --> 00:21:03,641
Let's dig in.

470
00:21:06,393 --> 00:21:07,767
[She Picks It Up With Her Hand]

471
00:21:07,767 --> 00:21:09,468
[And Takes A Big Bite]
Like that.

472
00:21:11,937 --> 00:21:16,475
[She Even Licks The Cream Off Her Fingers]

473
00:21:17,343 --> 00:21:18,744
It's very good.

474
00:21:18,744 --> 00:21:22,281
[Coffee Tastes Best]

475
00:21:22,281 --> 00:21:25,651
[When You Drink It With A Fork]

476
00:21:25,651 --> 00:21:26,691
Hello.

477
00:21:26,691 --> 00:21:30,489
Thanks so much, Gyu Seong.
We're here because of you.

478
00:21:30,489 --> 00:21:33,292
What a luxury.

479
00:21:33,292 --> 00:21:34,293
[My Sweet Nephew]

480
00:21:36,896 --> 00:21:38,964
- I like the latte since it's not sweet.
- What?

481
00:21:38,964 --> 00:21:40,032
It's not so sweet.

482
00:21:40,032 --> 00:21:42,601
[Thank You, My Dear Grandson]

483
00:21:42,601 --> 00:21:45,738
It pairs well with the desserts.

484
00:21:45,738 --> 00:21:48,864
- Did you enjoy it?
- Yes, thank you.

485
00:21:52,511 --> 00:21:56,982
[Family Time Made Sweeter By Dessert]

486
00:21:58,951 --> 00:22:00,786
One, two, three!

487
00:22:02,922 --> 00:22:03,989
It's here.

488
00:22:03,989 --> 00:22:05,057
Let's check it out.

489
00:22:05,057 --> 00:22:07,059
At Bonjour Bakery.

490
00:22:07,059 --> 00:22:08,394
Do you want to take a photo?

491
00:22:08,394 --> 00:22:11,397
[We Get Many Customers
Who Rarely Frequent Other Bakeries]

492
00:22:11,397 --> 00:22:12,730
Hi.

493
00:22:12,730 --> 00:22:14,133
[All Kinds Of Men Over 65 Years Old]

494
00:22:14,133 --> 00:22:15,968
[Come To Visit]
Hello.

495
00:22:15,968 --> 00:22:18,704
Can I just check your ID?

496
00:22:18,704 --> 00:22:20,272
You want to take the hat off?

497
00:22:20,272 --> 00:22:21,740
There we go. Sit down.

498
00:22:21,740 --> 00:22:23,609
- Have a seat.
- Move over.

499
00:22:23,609 --> 00:22:25,311
Take that off.

500
00:22:25,311 --> 00:22:26,885
Yes, let's unzip that.

501
00:22:26,885 --> 00:22:28,881
[An Old Man Who Takes Care Of His Grandson]

502
00:22:28,881 --> 00:22:30,382
There we go.

503
00:22:30,382 --> 00:22:31,884
[A Gray-Haired Romantic]

504
00:22:31,884 --> 00:22:36,689
[Who Lets His Wife Have The First Bite]

505
00:22:38,490 --> 00:22:40,693
[A Father Who Is Used To Waiting]

506
00:22:40,693 --> 00:22:44,496
[For His Daughter To Take A Picture First]

507
00:22:45,331 --> 00:22:51,103
[Friends Who Have A Blast
Just Hanging Out Together]

508
00:22:51,943 --> 00:22:53,572
[A Chatterbox Who Enjoys]

509
00:22:53,572 --> 00:22:57,710
[Talking Endlessly With His Middle-Aged Son]

510
00:23:00,846 --> 00:23:03,949
[And]

511
00:23:07,186 --> 00:23:08,587
That's what I'm saying.

512
00:23:08,587 --> 00:23:10,990
- Just have a bite of this.
- Look outside!

513
00:23:10,990 --> 00:23:12,491
[An Old Man Who Parks Naturally]

514
00:23:12,992 --> 00:23:14,393
Hello.

515
00:23:14,393 --> 00:23:16,228
[But Enters Awkwardly]

516
00:23:17,062 --> 00:23:20,299
[Im Chae Dong]

517
00:23:21,333 --> 00:23:23,903
[Looking Around]

518
00:23:23,903 --> 00:23:26,272
Hello, sir.

519
00:23:26,272 --> 00:23:28,507
Are you here alone?

520
00:23:28,507 --> 00:23:30,075
- Yes, I am.
- Come this way.

521
00:23:30,075 --> 00:23:32,970
Yes, take a seat here.

522
00:23:34,980 --> 00:23:36,515
[I Heard This Was A Bakery]

523
00:23:36,515 --> 00:23:39,718
[What's This For?]

524
00:23:39,718 --> 00:23:40,920
- This is-
- What's this?

525
00:23:40,920 --> 00:23:43,188
It's a warm towel.

526
00:23:43,188 --> 00:23:45,658
Use that to wipe your hands

527
00:23:45,658 --> 00:23:48,127
since you might touch the bread
with your hands.

528
00:23:48,127 --> 00:23:49,028
[He Wipes His Mouth Instead]

529
00:23:49,028 --> 00:23:50,629
What is this?

530
00:23:50,629 --> 00:23:52,932
It's the coffee list. This is an Americano.

531
00:23:52,932 --> 00:23:54,099
Americano?

532
00:23:54,099 --> 00:23:55,634
That's a type of coffee?

533
00:23:56,303 --> 00:23:57,670
[I Heard This Was A Bakery]
I don't drink coffee.

534
00:23:57,670 --> 00:23:58,804
[But It Sells Strange Things]

535
00:23:58,804 --> 00:23:59,972
In that case...

536
00:23:59,972 --> 00:24:01,974
We also serve hot teas.

537
00:24:03,943 --> 00:24:06,879
[What Is That?]

538
00:24:07,746 --> 00:24:10,716
[An Assortment Of Bread]

539
00:24:15,354 --> 00:24:18,958
[He Goes To The Display Case
Like A Moth To A Flame]

540
00:24:18,958 --> 00:24:21,093
What's this?

541
00:24:21,093 --> 00:24:23,595
This one here.

542
00:24:23,595 --> 00:24:25,664
What is it?

543
00:24:25,664 --> 00:24:29,735
That's a dessert called a Madeleine.

544
00:24:29,735 --> 00:24:33,172
[It Seems To Take His Fancy]

545
00:24:34,773 --> 00:24:36,942
[A Smooth And Glossy Exterior]

546
00:24:36,942 --> 00:24:38,243
[With A Clear Citron Fragrance]
It's citron-flavored.

547
00:24:38,243 --> 00:24:40,112
It's this one here.

548
00:24:42,414 --> 00:24:44,149
Give me that one.

549
00:24:44,149 --> 00:24:45,651
Give me this amount's worth.

550
00:24:45,651 --> 00:24:50,122
For 10,000 won,
you can have three of these.

551
00:24:50,122 --> 00:24:52,424
- It's only worth three of these?
- Yes.

552
00:24:52,424 --> 00:24:54,460
[Feeling Bad For Some Reason]

553
00:24:54,460 --> 00:24:56,095
Okay, give me that much.

554
00:24:56,095 --> 00:24:57,387
All right.

555
00:25:01,433 --> 00:25:05,204
[But We'll Give You
A Cup Of Tea On The House]

556
00:25:06,672 --> 00:25:09,241
- The tea is on the house, right?
- Yes, it's free.

557
00:25:09,241 --> 00:25:11,872
This is his 1,000 won change.

558
00:25:12,778 --> 00:25:14,913
[And]

559
00:25:14,913 --> 00:25:18,183
[Here Comes Another Solo Customer]

560
00:25:23,055 --> 00:25:24,556
Hello.

561
00:25:25,891 --> 00:25:28,360
Hello!

562
00:25:28,360 --> 00:25:30,095
Take a seat here.

563
00:25:30,095 --> 00:25:32,898
If you wait a moment,
I'll bring you the menu.

564
00:25:32,898 --> 00:25:34,333
[Ko Gwang Hyeon]

565
00:25:36,068 --> 00:25:38,404
- Here is a wet towel.
- Thank you.

566
00:25:39,872 --> 00:25:43,208
This is the coffee and drinks menu.

567
00:25:43,208 --> 00:25:45,511
I want a hot drip coffee.

568
00:25:45,511 --> 00:25:46,612
- Hot one?
- Yes.

569
00:25:46,612 --> 00:25:48,113
- Would you like black coffee?
- Yes.

570
00:25:48,113 --> 00:25:50,015
- Is black okay?
- Yes.

571
00:25:50,015 --> 00:25:52,985
As for the desserts,
we have Blueberry Éclair.

572
00:25:52,985 --> 00:25:54,820
How about Camellia Tart?

573
00:25:54,820 --> 00:25:55,821
I think I prefer this one.

574
00:25:55,821 --> 00:25:57,289
- You'd rather have that?
- Yes.

575
00:25:57,289 --> 00:25:59,758
- The Bonjour Blueberry Éclair?
- Yes.

576
00:25:59,758 --> 00:26:01,126
[A Man Who Knows His Mind]

577
00:26:01,126 --> 00:26:03,462
Okay, I'll bring it right over.

578
00:26:15,407 --> 00:26:17,476
[The Quiet Joy Of Eating Solo]

579
00:26:17,476 --> 00:26:20,913
[He Blissfully Zones Out For A Moment]

580
00:26:23,515 --> 00:26:26,518
[Bonjour Bakery]

581
00:26:31,857 --> 00:26:33,625
Here is your black coffee.

582
00:26:34,226 --> 00:26:37,563
And this is the Blueberry Éclair.

583
00:26:37,563 --> 00:26:41,533
Here is a knife and fork

584
00:26:41,533 --> 00:26:43,802
so you can cut it and eat it.

585
00:26:44,837 --> 00:26:47,372
- Enjoy.
- All right.

586
00:26:50,209 --> 00:26:52,945
[Knife And Fork At The Ready]

587
00:27:24,877 --> 00:27:26,151
[Just As He Tries To Take A Sip]

588
00:27:26,151 --> 00:27:28,147
- Is it to your liking?
- It's great.

589
00:27:28,147 --> 00:27:29,481
- Really?
- Yes.

590
00:27:29,481 --> 00:27:31,517
[2nd Attempt]
Where are you from? Are you local?

591
00:27:31,517 --> 00:27:32,484
Yes, I live in this area.

592
00:27:32,484 --> 00:27:34,887
[Failed]

593
00:27:36,788 --> 00:27:38,257
[Passing The Time With A Question]
Is it a busy day?

594
00:27:38,257 --> 00:27:40,025
Yes, it's been really busy.

595
00:27:40,025 --> 00:27:41,293
[Tries The Éclair]

596
00:27:45,464 --> 00:27:47,733
[3 Second Rule]

597
00:27:49,301 --> 00:27:52,104
[No One Saw That, Right?]

598
00:27:54,873 --> 00:27:57,342
[With Another Sip Of Coffee]

599
00:27:57,342 --> 00:28:00,879
[He Regains His Inner Peace]

600
00:28:05,217 --> 00:28:06,318
- It's tasty.
- Is it?

601
00:28:06,318 --> 00:28:08,086
- You were here yesterday, right?
- Yes.

602
00:28:08,086 --> 00:28:09,054
Thank you.

603
00:28:09,054 --> 00:28:11,056
- Oh, you were here yesterday?
- He was.

604
00:28:11,056 --> 00:28:14,126
[Yesterday Day Of The Opening]
Sorry to keep you waiting.

605
00:28:20,098 --> 00:28:23,769
[He Neatly Cuts The Bread Rolls]

606
00:28:26,405 --> 00:28:29,208
[Adds A Layer Of Strawberry Jam]

607
00:28:29,208 --> 00:28:31,276
[With Soft Dabs]

608
00:28:32,344 --> 00:28:35,647
[Elegantly Takes A Bite]

609
00:28:42,321 --> 00:28:46,625
[Fully Enjoying His Alone Time
In The Bakery]

610
00:28:49,461 --> 00:28:50,835
I came here alone.

611
00:28:50,835 --> 00:28:53,571
Good call. It's nice being alone.

612
00:28:55,106 --> 00:28:57,603
I should come here more often as a local.

613
00:28:57,603 --> 00:29:00,005
Thank you so much.

614
00:29:02,608 --> 00:29:05,177
Meanwhile.

615
00:29:05,177 --> 00:29:08,680
[This Customer Looks A Little Troubled]

616
00:29:12,017 --> 00:29:14,353
[A Fancy Bakery]

617
00:29:14,353 --> 00:29:17,556
[In Our Quiet Village?]

618
00:29:19,591 --> 00:29:23,462
[Lost In Thought]

619
00:29:24,963 --> 00:29:28,400
You can't make much money
in a countryside like this.

620
00:29:28,400 --> 00:29:30,736
There aren't enough people.
You're better off in the city.

621
00:29:30,736 --> 00:29:32,816
[Worried About The Wellbeing
Of The Young Café Staff]

622
00:29:34,606 --> 00:29:36,908
[We Appreciate Your Concern]

623
00:29:36,908 --> 00:29:40,145
[Let Us Take A Load Off Your Mind
With A Tasty Dessert]

624
00:29:41,513 --> 00:29:46,118
- Sir, this tea is on the house.
- Okay.

625
00:29:47,452 --> 00:29:49,688
If you end up with any leftovers,

626
00:29:49,688 --> 00:29:51,590
we'll wrap them up for you to go

627
00:29:51,590 --> 00:29:54,546
so you can finish the rest at home.

628
00:29:56,061 --> 00:29:58,830
[First A Sip To Quench His Thirst]

629
00:30:07,105 --> 00:30:08,940
[Break A Bit Off]

630
00:30:08,940 --> 00:30:12,811
[To See How It Tastes]

631
00:30:28,060 --> 00:30:30,329
Is it to your liking?

632
00:30:30,329 --> 00:30:32,076
Does it taste okay?

633
00:30:32,564 --> 00:30:34,066
What does it matter how it tastes,

634
00:30:34,066 --> 00:30:36,892
as long as it's edible?

635
00:30:37,836 --> 00:30:40,484
I'm glad it's edible.

636
00:30:51,650 --> 00:30:53,520
[And Just Like That]

637
00:30:53,520 --> 00:30:57,224
[He Finishes Off A Whole Madeleine]

638
00:31:01,693 --> 00:31:03,095
[Peaceful Sigh]

639
00:31:17,509 --> 00:31:18,910
Do you need a cash receipt?

640
00:31:19,411 --> 00:31:20,579
[Customer From The Next Table]
Enjoy your dessert.

641
00:31:20,579 --> 00:31:21,980
I will.

642
00:31:21,980 --> 00:31:23,215
Are you a local?

643
00:31:23,215 --> 00:31:24,349
- What?
- Do you live around here?

644
00:31:24,349 --> 00:31:25,817
Yes.

645
00:31:25,817 --> 00:31:27,552
- Where do you live?
- Sorry?

646
00:31:27,552 --> 00:31:29,821
You seem familiar, but maybe not.

647
00:31:29,821 --> 00:31:31,757
I'm from Sillim-myeon.

648
00:31:31,757 --> 00:31:33,024
- What?
- Byeoksong-ri.

649
00:31:33,024 --> 00:31:35,466
- That's my hometown.
- I see.

650
00:31:35,466 --> 00:31:37,519
I live in the town center now.

651
00:31:38,730 --> 00:31:40,132
You came all this way?

652
00:31:40,132 --> 00:31:41,969
It's just around the corner.

653
00:31:44,436 --> 00:31:47,205
I dropped by while passing by.

654
00:31:47,205 --> 00:31:49,274
Excuse me.

655
00:31:49,274 --> 00:31:50,842
- Should I wrap it up for you?
- Yes.

656
00:31:50,842 --> 00:31:53,412
Let me wrap it up for you.
It's a lot to eat alone.

657
00:31:53,412 --> 00:31:57,082
Take it home and have it for breakfast.

658
00:32:02,721 --> 00:32:05,891
<i>Elderly people can't eat that much.</i>

659
00:32:05,891 --> 00:32:08,827
<i>It's hard on their stomachs.</i>

660
00:32:09,428 --> 00:32:15,100
<i>My mother says it's hard to digest food.</i>

661
00:32:15,100 --> 00:32:20,539
<i>It's a big blessing to eat
and digest food comfortably.</i>

662
00:32:20,539 --> 00:32:23,208
[Bonjour Bakery]

663
00:32:23,842 --> 00:32:26,178
How old are you, sir?

664
00:32:26,178 --> 00:32:27,412
I'm 90 years old.

665
00:32:27,412 --> 00:32:28,904
Oh, gosh.

666
00:32:30,015 --> 00:32:31,950
Do you live alone?

667
00:32:31,950 --> 00:32:33,919
You mean, where is my wife?

668
00:32:33,919 --> 00:32:35,120
Yes.

669
00:32:35,120 --> 00:32:37,989
My wife is in heaven.

670
00:32:37,989 --> 00:32:40,091
I'm sorry.

671
00:32:40,091 --> 00:32:43,428
It must be hard living on your own.

672
00:32:43,428 --> 00:32:45,728
That's life for you.

673
00:32:47,550 --> 00:32:48,767
Goodbye, sir.

674
00:32:48,767 --> 00:32:50,836
- Thank you.
- No problem.

675
00:32:50,836 --> 00:32:52,980
Thank you for coming.

676
00:32:56,007 --> 00:32:57,909
Take care, sir.

677
00:32:58,677 --> 00:33:00,304
Thank you.

678
00:33:14,693 --> 00:33:17,047
It wasn't bad.

679
00:33:21,500 --> 00:33:25,270
[When Will You Have
The Leftover Madeleines?]

680
00:33:26,838 --> 00:33:29,641
I could eat some if I wake up at night.

681
00:33:29,641 --> 00:33:31,309
And I'll eat some more tomorrow.

682
00:33:31,309 --> 00:33:32,577
I'll store them well.

683
00:33:32,577 --> 00:33:34,875
I've lived alone for three years.

684
00:33:35,480 --> 00:33:37,549
<i>I have six children.</i>

685
00:33:37,549 --> 00:33:40,218
<i>I have 3 daughters and 3 sons.</i>

686
00:33:40,218 --> 00:33:41,987
- I have six children.
- I see.

687
00:33:41,987 --> 00:33:44,690
But they all live away from home now.

688
00:33:45,190 --> 00:33:48,426
They need to make a living, after all.

689
00:33:48,426 --> 00:33:50,328
So, it's just me.

690
00:33:50,328 --> 00:33:52,797
I have one healthcare nurse,

691
00:33:52,797 --> 00:33:54,566
but I live alone.

692
00:33:54,566 --> 00:33:57,802
There used to be
many people in this village,

693
00:33:57,802 --> 00:33:59,848
but now they're all...

694
00:34:00,705 --> 00:34:03,174
A lot of them have passed on,

695
00:34:03,174 --> 00:34:04,643
so there are few of us left.

696
00:34:04,643 --> 00:34:07,245
<i>There used to be many farmers here.</i>

697
00:34:07,245 --> 00:34:10,549
<i>But younger people need to make a living,</i>

698
00:34:10,549 --> 00:34:11,983
<i>so why should they stay in the country?</i>

699
00:34:11,983 --> 00:34:14,050
<i>They all move away.</i>

700
00:34:14,886 --> 00:34:17,255
It gets lonely.

701
00:34:17,255 --> 00:34:19,124
When I get sick,

702
00:34:19,124 --> 00:34:21,026
if I get a stomachache
in the middle of the night,

703
00:34:21,026 --> 00:34:23,828
I don't have anyone
to bring me a glass of warm water.

704
00:34:23,828 --> 00:34:25,764
Those moments are hard.

705
00:34:25,764 --> 00:34:28,433
I usually call up my children.

706
00:34:31,069 --> 00:34:35,140
- Since we're deep in the countryside...
- Yes?

707
00:34:35,140 --> 00:34:37,962
Getting so many visitors like this

708
00:34:37,962 --> 00:34:41,654
brings me a lot of joy.

709
00:34:42,080 --> 00:34:44,155
- Will you come by again?
- Yes.

710
00:34:44,155 --> 00:34:45,628
All right.

711
00:34:47,319 --> 00:34:49,888
Get some rest, sir.

712
00:34:49,888 --> 00:34:51,156
Bye.

713
00:34:53,358 --> 00:34:55,360
- Take good care of yourself.
- Okay.

714
00:35:11,977 --> 00:35:17,983
[Bonjour Bakery]

715
00:35:18,883 --> 00:35:21,486
[Meanwhile In The Kitchen]

716
00:35:22,621 --> 00:35:26,391
[The Madeleine Station
Keeps Working Without A Break]

717
00:35:28,326 --> 00:35:33,698
[The Madeleine Molds Are Buttered]

718
00:35:37,302 --> 00:35:40,805
[40g Of Batter Are Portioned Into Each Mold]

719
00:35:41,773 --> 00:35:46,945
[The Batter Is Uniformly Shaped
And Placed On A Sheet Pan Or Inside A Mold]

720
00:35:48,413 --> 00:35:50,382
[The Key To This Step]

721
00:35:50,382 --> 00:35:53,685
[Is To Portion The Batter Evenly]

722
00:35:55,754 --> 00:35:57,856
[Portioning Step Complete]

723
00:35:59,658 --> 00:36:03,695
[Rest In The Freezer For 15 Minutes]

724
00:36:05,530 --> 00:36:08,566
- I should have had breakfast.
- This morning?

725
00:36:08,566 --> 00:36:11,102
- Did you not eat anything?
- No, I didn't.

726
00:36:11,670 --> 00:36:13,238
[Ki Taek's Sales Pitch]
Would you like the leftover eggs?

727
00:36:13,238 --> 00:36:14,472
You have it.

728
00:36:14,472 --> 00:36:15,940
[Sales Pitch Failed]

729
00:36:15,940 --> 00:36:17,676
It will help... Okay.

730
00:36:17,676 --> 00:36:19,411
Would you like something else instead?

731
00:36:19,411 --> 00:36:21,413
[Ki Taek's Still Concerned]
No, thanks.

732
00:36:21,413 --> 00:36:23,581
[I'll Wait For Dinner]
I'll have a proper meal later.

733
00:36:23,581 --> 00:36:25,150
Okay.

734
00:36:26,685 --> 00:36:29,621
[The 15 Minute Break Is Over]

735
00:36:33,224 --> 00:36:37,462
[The Batter Goes In The Oven For Baking]

736
00:36:46,538 --> 00:36:49,841
[The Batter Rises Inside The Oven]

737
00:36:52,243 --> 00:36:56,147
[They Have Risen Into Beautiful Madeleines]

738
00:36:56,848 --> 00:36:59,784
<i>[Bokbunja</i> Glaze]

739
00:37:00,919 --> 00:37:06,624
[The Madeleines Are Glazed
Once They Are Fully Cooled]

740
00:37:09,027 --> 00:37:12,330
[The Evenly Coated Bright Red Glaze]

741
00:37:14,505 --> 00:37:15,665
[Adds A Sweet And Sour Touch]

742
00:37:21,906 --> 00:37:24,142
- Yes, get it into the grooves.
- Right.

743
00:37:24,976 --> 00:37:27,479
- Glaze the front and back.
- Okay.

744
00:37:51,069 --> 00:37:53,738
[Made With Several Brushstrokes]

745
00:37:55,774 --> 00:37:58,376
[A Glossy Red Coating]

746
00:38:02,914 --> 00:38:03,982
All right.

747
00:38:03,982 --> 00:38:09,320
[The Glazed Madeleines
Are Briefly Baked Again To Dry]

748
00:38:14,058 --> 00:38:18,229
[Bonjour <i>Bokbunja</i> Madeleine]

749
00:38:19,364 --> 00:38:20,932
- There's still a long way to go.
- It's 5 p.m.

750
00:38:20,932 --> 00:38:23,372
- We have one hour left.
- There's an hour left until closing.

751
00:38:29,874 --> 00:38:31,242
Welcome!

752
00:38:31,242 --> 00:38:32,644
Come this way.

753
00:38:32,644 --> 00:38:33,812
We need to check your ID.

754
00:38:33,812 --> 00:38:36,614
- We can sit over there.
- That's right.

755
00:38:36,614 --> 00:38:39,726
It's the perfect table for two.

756
00:38:42,020 --> 00:38:47,225
- We should have a coffee now we're here.
- Yes.

757
00:38:47,225 --> 00:38:51,529
- They also accept the Gochang Gift Card.
- What?

758
00:38:51,529 --> 00:38:55,166
[Authorized Gift Card Retailers]
They accept the Gochang Sarang Gift Card.

759
00:38:55,166 --> 00:38:57,569
There's a bit of a chill today.

760
00:38:57,569 --> 00:38:58,736
Yeah, it's a bit chilly.

761
00:38:58,736 --> 00:39:01,406
I heard it would be warm today.

762
00:39:01,406 --> 00:39:04,075
It's a bit too cold.

763
00:39:04,075 --> 00:39:06,604
It's making my throat dry.

764
00:39:06,604 --> 00:39:09,707
[The Wind Is Rather Brisk Today]

765
00:39:11,749 --> 00:39:13,625
What should we eat?

766
00:39:14,886 --> 00:39:17,989
I don't know.
I've never tried any of these.

767
00:39:18,556 --> 00:39:21,726
[Something Grabs His Attention]
This one is strawberry...

768
00:39:21,726 --> 00:39:22,861
"Camellia Tart."

769
00:39:22,861 --> 00:39:25,230
- Should we get the Blueberry Éclair?
- Camellia Tart.

770
00:39:25,230 --> 00:39:27,465
This one?

771
00:39:27,465 --> 00:39:29,567
Yeah, I think that's the right choice.

772
00:39:29,567 --> 00:39:31,436
What coffee do you want?

773
00:39:32,070 --> 00:39:34,305
Let's just have an Americano.

774
00:39:34,305 --> 00:39:35,976
Sure.

775
00:39:36,708 --> 00:39:40,211
[Manager Hee Ae Has Been Paying Attention]

776
00:39:40,745 --> 00:39:42,247
[She Goes To Get Their Order]

777
00:39:42,247 --> 00:39:43,681
Let's just have an Americano.

778
00:39:43,681 --> 00:39:47,485
- You'd like the Americano?
- Yes, we'll take that.

779
00:39:47,485 --> 00:39:50,188
Would you like it hot?

780
00:39:50,188 --> 00:39:52,790
- Yes, it should be hot.
- Okay.

781
00:39:52,790 --> 00:39:54,359
- Should I order this?
- Yeah.

782
00:39:54,359 --> 00:39:56,463
One Camellia Tart.

783
00:39:56,463 --> 00:39:59,130
Wait, should we get one of each?

784
00:39:59,130 --> 00:40:01,799
Do we share one between us?

785
00:40:01,799 --> 00:40:02,867
You want to get two?

786
00:40:02,867 --> 00:40:04,702
Did you want to share one?

787
00:40:04,702 --> 00:40:05,970
Yeah, well...

788
00:40:05,970 --> 00:40:08,312
If we eat too much,
we won't be able to eat dinner.

789
00:40:08,312 --> 00:40:11,442
Why can't we eat dinner?

790
00:40:11,442 --> 00:40:13,511
[You Want To Share These Tiny Desserts?]

791
00:40:13,511 --> 00:40:16,488
A Sudden Debate Over Dessert-Sharing.

792
00:40:18,449 --> 00:40:20,952
- We'll take one of each.
- Okay.

793
00:40:20,952 --> 00:40:22,353
[They End Up Ordering Both]

794
00:40:22,353 --> 00:40:23,655
[2 Hot Americanos, 1 Camellia Tart,
1 Blueberry Éclair]

795
00:40:23,655 --> 00:40:25,189
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

796
00:40:25,629 --> 00:40:27,625
- What did they order?
- Two Americanos.

797
00:40:27,625 --> 00:40:29,471
- They want it hot.
- Hot? Okay.

798
00:40:30,061 --> 00:40:33,064
Lately, my arms ache like crazy
after a little bit of hoeing.

799
00:40:34,098 --> 00:40:36,801
Even if I want to go out,
I don't have anywhere to go.

800
00:40:36,801 --> 00:40:39,837
I just go out anyway.

801
00:40:39,837 --> 00:40:41,779
Whether I'm walking around the village

802
00:40:41,779 --> 00:40:44,108
or spending time in the Village Hall,

803
00:40:44,108 --> 00:40:46,044
there's nothing much to do.

804
00:40:46,044 --> 00:40:50,315
It's not any better in the Village Hall.

805
00:40:50,315 --> 00:40:53,665
But I get bored at home alone.

806
00:40:55,019 --> 00:40:59,190
[Caught Up In The Chaos Of Life,
Time Has Passed By In A Flash]

807
00:41:00,124 --> 00:41:03,928
[Days That Used To Feel Too Short]

808
00:41:03,928 --> 00:41:08,132
[Are Now Too Long To Fill]

809
00:41:08,967 --> 00:41:12,737
[What Can You Do]

810
00:41:12,737 --> 00:41:17,275
[With All This Spare Time?]

811
00:41:19,010 --> 00:41:22,547
[Every Day Is The Same]

812
00:41:22,547 --> 00:41:28,386
[Time Spent Quietly Without Much Ado]

813
00:41:29,253 --> 00:41:30,421
Here you go.

814
00:41:32,523 --> 00:41:33,691
My goodness.

815
00:41:33,691 --> 00:41:35,176
Enjoy.

816
00:41:36,494 --> 00:41:40,698
- Should we give it a taste?
- All right.

817
00:41:41,432 --> 00:41:43,365
You're not going to offer me a bite?

818
00:41:52,143 --> 00:41:54,345
It's a very fancy dessert.

819
00:41:54,345 --> 00:41:56,347
Let's split this.

820
00:41:56,347 --> 00:41:58,916
Take half of this.

821
00:41:58,916 --> 00:42:02,286
No need to cut it in half. Just eat it.

822
00:42:02,854 --> 00:42:04,422
Don't eat it all.

823
00:42:04,422 --> 00:42:05,990
[I Want To Try Both]

824
00:42:05,990 --> 00:42:08,770
Take a piece of this, then.

825
00:42:11,062 --> 00:42:13,798
This one's smaller than that one.

826
00:42:14,265 --> 00:42:16,000
You should take a big piece.

827
00:42:16,000 --> 00:42:18,269
It feels like I'm losing out.

828
00:42:18,269 --> 00:42:20,172
- Yours is bigger.
- Exactly.

829
00:42:28,012 --> 00:42:30,882
- It's very sweet.
- Yes.

830
00:42:34,152 --> 00:42:36,888
[The Perfect Time For A Sip Of Americano]

831
00:42:36,888 --> 00:42:38,056
Take a sip.

832
00:42:38,056 --> 00:42:39,791
The coffee is nice.

833
00:42:39,791 --> 00:42:42,226
I like that the coffee's not too sweet.

834
00:42:42,226 --> 00:42:43,628
How is it?

835
00:42:44,896 --> 00:42:46,164
It's all right.

836
00:42:46,164 --> 00:42:49,167
Are you usually a dessert person?

837
00:42:49,167 --> 00:42:50,701
- Yes, I am.
- I see.

838
00:42:50,701 --> 00:42:52,437
It's nice and sweet.

839
00:42:52,437 --> 00:42:55,422
- It's sweet and tasty.
- I'm glad you like it.

840
00:43:01,145 --> 00:43:06,751
[Eating Up Every Crumb]

841
00:43:06,751 --> 00:43:08,519
We'd better not let any go to waste.

842
00:43:08,519 --> 00:43:11,522
This should be enough.

843
00:43:13,791 --> 00:43:16,861
We won't need dinner after this.

844
00:43:16,861 --> 00:43:18,963
Would you like an iced Americano?

845
00:43:18,963 --> 00:43:20,431
Or something else to drink?

846
00:43:20,431 --> 00:43:22,667
I want coffee,
but I might not be able to sleep.

847
00:43:22,667 --> 00:43:23,734
But I want a tiny sip.

848
00:43:23,734 --> 00:43:25,636
- How about decaf?
- Why about something sweet?

849
00:43:25,636 --> 00:43:28,005
- Decaf sounds good.
- Okay.

850
00:43:28,005 --> 00:43:29,607
You're the best.

851
00:43:29,607 --> 00:43:31,275
- I'm running low on steam.
- Okay.

852
00:43:31,275 --> 00:43:32,510
I'm losing focus.

853
00:43:32,510 --> 00:43:35,012
- You're doing great. Keep going.
- I'm telling you, Hee Ae...

854
00:43:35,012 --> 00:43:38,015
- Let's relax with coffee after closing.
- Yes.

855
00:43:38,015 --> 00:43:39,743
Definitely.

856
00:43:39,743 --> 00:43:43,031
- We worked really hard today.
- As heaven is our witness.

857
00:43:44,088 --> 00:43:46,724
[5:50 p.m.]

858
00:43:46,724 --> 00:43:49,193
- Thank you.
- Goodbye.

859
00:43:49,193 --> 00:43:50,862
- Thank you.
- Bye.

860
00:43:50,862 --> 00:43:52,797
- Goodbye.
- Thank you for coming.

861
00:43:52,797 --> 00:43:53,798
Thank you.

862
00:43:53,798 --> 00:43:55,399
[The Customers Leave One By One]

863
00:43:55,399 --> 00:43:57,034
Thank you.

864
00:43:57,034 --> 00:43:58,336
- Bye.
- Goodbye.

865
00:43:59,337 --> 00:44:00,271
Here...

866
00:44:00,271 --> 00:44:01,772
- Thank you.
- Thank you for coming.

867
00:44:01,772 --> 00:44:03,574
Goodbye.

868
00:44:03,574 --> 00:44:05,076
Thank you.

869
00:44:05,076 --> 00:44:07,078
- Have a safe trip home.
- Thank you.

870
00:44:07,078 --> 00:44:08,379
Get home safely.

871
00:44:08,379 --> 00:44:09,714
- Bye.
- Thank you.

872
00:44:09,714 --> 00:44:11,060
Thank you.

873
00:44:13,918 --> 00:44:19,423
[We Hope That Today's Sweet Desserts
Brought You A Slice Of Happiness]

874
00:44:19,891 --> 00:44:22,560
[6 p.m. Closing Time]

875
00:44:28,599 --> 00:44:31,869
[A Senior Lady Comes By After Closing]

876
00:44:33,404 --> 00:44:36,207
[She's Owned This Building
Since It Was A Corner Store]

877
00:44:37,975 --> 00:44:41,979
[Now A Regular At Revived Bonjour Bakery]

878
00:44:45,789 --> 00:44:47,852
- Hello.
- I came to get some more bread.

879
00:44:47,852 --> 00:44:48,953
Sorry?

880
00:44:48,953 --> 00:44:51,289
- I wanted to buy one more to take away.
- You want to buy one more?

881
00:44:51,289 --> 00:44:53,457
[We Are Closed]
What did you like the best?

882
00:44:53,457 --> 00:44:54,592
The one in the paper bag.

883
00:44:54,592 --> 00:44:55,660
Paper bag?

884
00:44:55,660 --> 00:44:57,361
- Yes.
- Which one was that?

885
00:44:57,361 --> 00:44:58,829
I wonder which one you mean.

886
00:44:58,829 --> 00:45:00,631
Why don't you come in?

887
00:45:00,631 --> 00:45:02,547
Which one are you thinking of?

888
00:45:03,167 --> 00:45:04,936
- There it is.
- Which one?

889
00:45:04,936 --> 00:45:07,271
- That one over there.
- The bread rolls.

890
00:45:08,072 --> 00:45:10,341
[The Owner Is Back To Help Us Out Again]

891
00:45:10,341 --> 00:45:11,738
How much is it?

892
00:45:12,810 --> 00:45:15,947
We're closed for the day.

893
00:45:15,947 --> 00:45:17,515
This one is on the house.

894
00:45:17,515 --> 00:45:18,916
But you must come again tomorrow.

895
00:45:18,916 --> 00:45:20,084
- What?
- Just take it.

896
00:45:20,084 --> 00:45:21,719
I can't do that.

897
00:45:21,719 --> 00:45:23,254
It's fine. Just come by tomorrow.

898
00:45:23,254 --> 00:45:25,690
Promise me you'll come.

899
00:45:25,690 --> 00:45:26,958
- Let me pay you.
- Promise.

900
00:45:26,958 --> 00:45:28,159
No, I won't take your money.

901
00:45:28,159 --> 00:45:29,427
Promise me.

902
00:45:29,427 --> 00:45:30,595
Thank you.

903
00:45:30,595 --> 00:45:32,897
- Come by again tomorrow.
- Okay.

904
00:45:32,897 --> 00:45:35,933
[She Feels Sorry]
I wanted to buy more since it's so tasty.

905
00:45:35,933 --> 00:45:37,168
- Do you want some jam?
- What?

906
00:45:37,168 --> 00:45:39,188
Jam. Wait a minute.

907
00:45:42,406 --> 00:45:44,408
- I put in two jam pods.
- Okay.

908
00:45:44,408 --> 00:45:45,576
Enjoy.

909
00:45:45,576 --> 00:45:46,978
You'll come tomorrow, right?

910
00:45:46,978 --> 00:45:48,684
I'm not taking that.

911
00:45:50,214 --> 00:45:52,283
- See you tomorrow.
- All right.

912
00:45:52,283 --> 00:45:53,851
- Get home safely.
- Bye.

913
00:45:58,422 --> 00:46:01,043
- Great job, everyone!
- We're closed for the day.

914
00:46:03,761 --> 00:46:05,363
- Good work.
- Come on.

915
00:46:05,363 --> 00:46:07,298
[Closing Ceremony]
Great job.

916
00:46:07,298 --> 00:46:09,200
- Great job.
- Thanks for your hard work.

917
00:46:09,200 --> 00:46:11,936
[Proud Ki Taek]

918
00:46:12,770 --> 00:46:15,740
[In Need Of A Pick-Me-Up
Now That The Day Is Over]

919
00:46:15,740 --> 00:46:16,874
[Scanning The Display]

920
00:46:16,874 --> 00:46:18,109
[There's One Blueberry Éclair Left]

921
00:46:18,109 --> 00:46:20,611
I haven't tried that yet.

922
00:46:20,611 --> 00:46:23,814
I'm going to eat all the leftovers,
including that Blueberry Éclair.

923
00:46:25,116 --> 00:46:26,450
One Blueberry Éclair.

924
00:46:27,084 --> 00:46:30,621
[He Fetches The Blueberry Éclair
For The Hall Team]

925
00:46:34,191 --> 00:46:36,794
It's a Blueberry Éclair!

926
00:46:37,461 --> 00:46:38,929
Do you want an iced Americano?

927
00:46:38,929 --> 00:46:39,930
Yes, please.

928
00:46:39,930 --> 00:46:41,565
- Decaf?
- Yes!

929
00:46:41,565 --> 00:46:43,501
[The Hall Team Makes Drinks
For The Kitchen Team]

930
00:46:43,501 --> 00:46:44,835
[They Bolster Each Other Up
With Dessert And Coffee]

931
00:46:44,835 --> 00:46:47,004
- Drink that.
- You should try it.

932
00:46:47,004 --> 00:46:48,406
It's a mini party.

933
00:46:48,406 --> 00:46:51,242
[Feeling Blissful]

934
00:46:53,344 --> 00:46:55,546
This looks so tasty.

935
00:46:59,684 --> 00:47:01,252
You cried?

936
00:47:01,252 --> 00:47:02,520
Because I might steal a bite?

937
00:47:03,187 --> 00:47:05,790
Right? I told you it's unbelievable.

938
00:47:07,725 --> 00:47:08,993
My goodness.

939
00:47:11,662 --> 00:47:13,331
It really hits you.

940
00:47:13,331 --> 00:47:15,099
I just got a dopamine spike.

941
00:47:15,099 --> 00:47:16,300
This is delicious.

942
00:47:16,300 --> 00:47:18,469
- It's not too sweet, either.
- Try this.

943
00:47:18,469 --> 00:47:21,372
- It's not too sugary.
- No, it's not.

944
00:47:21,372 --> 00:47:23,874
It applies to all our cakes and pastries.

945
00:47:23,874 --> 00:47:25,751
None of them are too sweet.

946
00:47:27,478 --> 00:47:29,866
This is the real deal.

947
00:47:32,583 --> 00:47:33,806
Is it okay?

948
00:47:34,652 --> 00:47:35,720
It's way better than okay.

949
00:47:35,720 --> 00:47:37,855
- It's delicious.
- It's so tasty.

950
00:47:37,855 --> 00:47:40,458
- You did an incredible job.
- You know we're honest critics.

951
00:47:42,059 --> 00:47:45,162
It's amazing. Even in France...

952
00:47:45,162 --> 00:47:46,530
Even French people...

953
00:47:46,530 --> 00:47:48,599
Even in France,
I've never had anything this tasty.

954
00:47:48,599 --> 00:47:50,679
Me neither. Seriously.

955
00:47:50,679 --> 00:47:53,171
I think it would be a huge hit over there.

956
00:47:55,306 --> 00:47:57,475
[Pleased By The High Praise]
This is unbelievable.

957
00:48:00,244 --> 00:48:02,346
[Why Does It Feel Like Something Is Missing?]

958
00:48:02,346 --> 00:48:04,014
- Can you ring the bell?
- Sure.

959
00:48:04,014 --> 00:48:05,583
Should we get a breath of fresh air?

960
00:48:05,583 --> 00:48:08,185
- Great idea.
- Let's sit outside.

961
00:48:08,185 --> 00:48:09,987
- Let's go outside.
- I'm ringing the bell.

962
00:48:09,987 --> 00:48:11,856
[Ding Ding]

963
00:48:12,256 --> 00:48:14,091
[Another Long, Hard Day]

964
00:48:15,666 --> 00:48:16,897
<i>- Wait a minute.
- Great job.</i>

965
00:48:16,897 --> 00:48:19,230
[Sunset Behind Bangjangsan Mountain]
<i>The sun is setting right on cue.</i>

966
00:48:19,230 --> 00:48:20,297
<i>It's slowly sinking.</i>

967
00:48:20,297 --> 00:48:21,298
- Over there?
- Yes.

968
00:48:21,298 --> 00:48:23,067
Isn't it the perfect moment
for dinner and drinks?

969
00:48:23,067 --> 00:48:24,635
What do you mean, "It's thinking?"

970
00:48:24,635 --> 00:48:26,373
- It's sinking.
- That's what you meant.

971
00:48:26,373 --> 00:48:28,152
[A Side Effect Of Working Hard]
My gosh.

972
00:48:29,206 --> 00:48:31,642
<i>We must go for dinner and drinks!</i>

973
00:48:31,642 --> 00:48:33,477
<i>It's a must!</i>

974
00:48:33,477 --> 00:48:36,480
<i>- It's not up for debate.
- It's non-negotiable.</i>

975
00:48:37,681 --> 00:48:39,150
- Hee Ae.
- Yes?

976
00:48:39,150 --> 00:48:44,755
I heard there's a really tasty
pork belly joint near here.

977
00:48:44,755 --> 00:48:46,023
Hooray!

978
00:48:46,023 --> 00:48:48,515
<i>What more is there to life? Let's enjoy it.</i>

979
00:48:51,429 --> 00:48:53,197
This is so good.

980
00:48:54,932 --> 00:48:56,867
[The Day's Fatigue Melts Away]

981
00:48:56,867 --> 00:48:59,870
[At The Sound Of Pork Simmering]

982
00:49:04,742 --> 00:49:06,211
It's so tasty.

983
00:49:10,080 --> 00:49:12,082
[This Is The Stuff]

984
00:49:12,683 --> 00:49:15,519
[A Piece Of Pork Belly]

985
00:49:15,519 --> 00:49:18,823
[A Piece Of Wild Garlic Leaves]

986
00:49:18,823 --> 00:49:20,591
[A Clove Of Garlic]

987
00:49:22,359 --> 00:49:27,565
[The Perfect Combination]

988
00:49:39,910 --> 00:49:45,049
The Camellia Tart and Green Barley Tart
are so hard to make.

989
00:49:45,049 --> 00:49:46,450
They take forever.

990
00:49:46,450 --> 00:49:48,986
Adding each topping with tweezers.

991
00:49:51,121 --> 00:49:54,625
Our work is time-consuming too.

992
00:49:54,625 --> 00:49:56,694
- Did you see that, Seon Ho?
- Hee Ae, doesn't it take...

993
00:49:56,694 --> 00:49:58,562
Your manager just snorted.

994
00:49:58,562 --> 00:50:00,564
[She's Embarrassed]
Tell him, Hee Ae! Our job isn't easy.

995
00:50:00,564 --> 00:50:03,067
Listen. She wishes she could agree with you...

996
00:50:03,067 --> 00:50:05,236
- Tell him steaming milk is hard work.
- Hey.

997
00:50:05,236 --> 00:50:06,837
- It takes skill.
- Why can't you tell him?

998
00:50:06,837 --> 00:50:08,726
Why aren't you saying anything?

999
00:50:13,110 --> 00:50:14,912
<i>- Great work, everyone.
- Good job.</i>

1000
00:50:14,912 --> 00:50:16,580
<i>Great work.</i>

1001
00:50:21,919 --> 00:50:23,053
Do you want beer, Seung Won?

1002
00:50:23,053 --> 00:50:24,522
Of course!

1003
00:50:25,556 --> 00:50:27,691
- Of course, I do.
- Ki Taek, you'll have one too, right?

1004
00:50:27,691 --> 00:50:28,959
Yes, please.

1005
00:50:28,959 --> 00:50:31,962
Now that we're here...

1006
00:50:31,962 --> 00:50:33,264
- Yes?
- Yes?

1007
00:50:33,264 --> 00:50:35,900
It feels like we're on a trip together.

1008
00:50:35,900 --> 00:50:37,902
Don't you think?

1009
00:50:37,902 --> 00:50:41,020
We should sit on the floor, right?

1010
00:50:42,706 --> 00:50:44,008
It's like a freshman party.

1011
00:50:44,008 --> 00:50:46,634
Right? It's so nice.

1012
00:50:48,445 --> 00:50:50,114
Hey, Ki Taek.

1013
00:50:50,114 --> 00:50:51,382
Why are you so strong? Come closer.

1014
00:50:51,382 --> 00:50:52,783
You're so fit.

1015
00:50:52,783 --> 00:50:53,951
- I'm not that fit.
- Have a beer.

1016
00:50:53,951 --> 00:50:56,720
I forgot to bring clothes.

1017
00:50:56,720 --> 00:50:57,988
I didn't bring anything to sleep in.

1018
00:50:57,988 --> 00:51:00,057
- Really?
- Yes, I didn't bring pajamas.

1019
00:51:00,057 --> 00:51:02,293
I'm going to just sleep in this.

1020
00:51:04,495 --> 00:51:06,297
It's so challenging.

1021
00:51:07,131 --> 00:51:09,600
[Does He Mean Acting?]

1022
00:51:10,234 --> 00:51:12,570
- There are easy-to-bake goods.
- Yes.

1023
00:51:12,570 --> 00:51:13,971
[He Means The Desserts]
But no one orders those.

1024
00:51:13,971 --> 00:51:15,339
[Seung Won Finds Them Tricky]
They order the tricky tarts.

1025
00:51:15,339 --> 00:51:16,740
Yes, the pretty ones.

1026
00:51:16,740 --> 00:51:18,952
- Green Barley Tart.
- Everyone likes the tarts.

1027
00:51:21,512 --> 00:51:23,080
Of course,

1028
00:51:23,080 --> 00:51:25,816
the more I do it, the more I feel like,

1029
00:51:25,816 --> 00:51:30,154
"This isn't so hard."

1030
00:51:30,154 --> 00:51:32,790
When we made the desserts today-

1031
00:51:32,790 --> 00:51:34,258
- You get used to it, right?
- Yes.

1032
00:51:34,258 --> 00:51:38,562
Now I have a better idea of how to help
with the recipes for each menu item.

1033
00:51:38,562 --> 00:51:41,705
I get what to do and get on with it.

1034
00:51:41,705 --> 00:51:46,330
We have to make Green Barley
and Camellia Tarts daily.

1035
00:51:46,330 --> 00:51:48,339
Yes, that's hard.

1036
00:51:48,339 --> 00:51:51,342
That's no easy feat.

1037
00:51:52,610 --> 00:51:54,011
It's overwhelming.

1038
00:51:54,011 --> 00:51:55,446
The recipes are also so diverse.

1039
00:51:55,446 --> 00:51:57,047
[Let's Give It Our All Again Tomorrow]

1040
00:52:10,027 --> 00:52:14,131
[It's The Start Of Another Exciting Day]

1041
00:52:25,943 --> 00:52:28,178
[Bonjour Bakery]

1042
00:52:28,178 --> 00:52:30,748
[What's On The Menu Today?]

1043
00:52:32,316 --> 00:52:37,154
[Bonjour Bakery Has Quickly Become
The Local Watering Hole]

1044
00:52:40,557 --> 00:52:43,460
It's especially rewarding
when a customer who came alone

1045
00:52:43,460 --> 00:52:45,827
buys things to take away.

1046
00:52:49,066 --> 00:52:50,601
To be honest,

1047
00:52:50,601 --> 00:52:53,170
I feel sad seeing grandmas come in alone.

1048
00:52:53,170 --> 00:52:54,972
Because...

1049
00:52:54,972 --> 00:52:58,008
My grandmother recently passed away.

1050
00:52:58,008 --> 00:53:00,811
Seeing them reminds me of her.

1051
00:53:02,513 --> 00:53:05,816
I didn't think about it much
until I came here.

1052
00:53:07,270 --> 00:53:10,069
I feel a bit regretful.

1053
00:53:10,069 --> 00:53:12,623
It's nice walking to work together.

1054
00:53:12,623 --> 00:53:15,426
- I feel more relaxed.
- Yes, I feel a bit more reflective.

1055
00:53:15,426 --> 00:53:16,706
[Why Seon Ho Cared For Grandmas]

1056
00:53:18,529 --> 00:53:21,386
I'm in a good mood,
and the weather's great.

1057
00:53:22,566 --> 00:53:24,214
It's another day, so...

1058
00:53:25,069 --> 00:53:26,036
A snapshot before we open.

1059
00:53:26,036 --> 00:53:28,272
Let me take a photo of you doing that.

1060
00:53:28,872 --> 00:53:33,343
[Ki Taek Takes A Picture
Of Seon Ho Taking A Snapshot]

1061
00:53:33,343 --> 00:53:36,052
[Trying To Get The Perfect Shot]

1062
00:53:36,052 --> 00:53:38,382
- You stand over there.
- It came out nice.

1063
00:53:38,382 --> 00:53:41,885
[A Wholesome Relay]

1064
00:53:42,619 --> 00:53:44,733
I'm a great photographer.

1065
00:53:46,623 --> 00:53:48,092
[An Interesting Angle]

1066
00:53:48,092 --> 00:53:50,794
[Putting His Back Into It]

1067
00:53:53,430 --> 00:53:55,799
Maybe I should retake...

1068
00:53:55,799 --> 00:53:57,987
Oh, I did a decent job.

1069
00:53:57,987 --> 00:54:00,637
[Ki Taek And Seon Ho's Handiwork]
<i>I did a pretty good job.</i>

1070
00:54:00,637 --> 00:54:02,106
<i>Trust me. I've got skills.</i>

1071
00:54:02,106 --> 00:54:04,608
<i>- Take a look.
- I got the shot. I'll send it to you.</i>

1072
00:54:05,509 --> 00:54:07,177
We're ready for work.

1073
00:54:07,177 --> 00:54:08,746
Good morning.

1074
00:54:08,746 --> 00:54:10,080
[They've Entered The Bakery]

1075
00:54:11,448 --> 00:54:13,150
Do you want a coffee?

1076
00:54:13,150 --> 00:54:14,952
- Yes, please.
- Okay.

1077
00:54:14,952 --> 00:54:16,353
Do you want some eggs?

1078
00:54:16,353 --> 00:54:18,489
- I'd love some.
- Okay.

1079
00:54:18,489 --> 00:54:20,657
What about the blueberry smoothie?
It's a no, right?

1080
00:54:20,657 --> 00:54:23,060
- No, I'll have them.
- Okay, because I'm making one for myself.

1081
00:54:23,060 --> 00:54:24,561
[Hurry Before He Changes His Mind]
I like that smoothie.

1082
00:54:24,561 --> 00:54:26,830
[Ki Taek Is Happy To Get A Breakfast Order]

1083
00:54:26,830 --> 00:54:29,233
[Chicken Corn Dogs]

1084
00:54:38,008 --> 00:54:42,012
[Now He Whips It Up In No Time]

1085
00:54:42,513 --> 00:54:45,282
[Meanwhile Seon Ho]

1086
00:54:47,117 --> 00:54:49,987
[Makes Coffee For Ki Taek]

1087
00:54:53,423 --> 00:54:59,196
[He Puts His Heart Into It]

1088
00:55:08,305 --> 00:55:12,576
[The Smell Of Coffee
Fills The Bakery Early In The Morning]

1089
00:55:16,613 --> 00:55:21,285
[The Heartfelt Cup Of Coffee Is Ready]

1090
00:55:26,423 --> 00:55:28,192
Ki Taek.

1091
00:55:28,192 --> 00:55:29,293
[Perfect Timing]
Yes?

1092
00:55:29,293 --> 00:55:31,128
Thank you. I appreciate it.

1093
00:55:31,128 --> 00:55:32,462
- Can I eat this?
- Yes.

1094
00:55:32,462 --> 00:55:33,931
Thank you.

1095
00:55:33,931 --> 00:55:35,265
[A Heartwarming Exchange]

1096
00:55:37,634 --> 00:55:39,136
[Feeling Nervous]

1097
00:55:39,136 --> 00:55:40,070
Is it okay?

1098
00:55:40,070 --> 00:55:41,772
- I really like this smoothie.
- Do you?

1099
00:55:41,772 --> 00:55:43,373
- That's a relief.
- It's so good.

1100
00:55:43,373 --> 00:55:45,943
[Pleased By Seon Ho's Compliment]

1101
00:55:45,943 --> 00:55:48,545
[Might As Well Boil Some Eggs Too]
<i>The eggs are...</i>

1102
00:55:49,880 --> 00:55:52,950
[Seriously Focused]

1103
00:55:52,950 --> 00:55:54,398
Seon Ho!

1104
00:55:55,085 --> 00:55:57,487
- Yes?
- Do you want a boiled egg?

1105
00:55:57,487 --> 00:55:58,684
Yes, please.

1106
00:55:58,684 --> 00:55:59,756
I just boiled them.

1107
00:55:59,756 --> 00:56:01,325
- They're ready?
- Yes.

1108
00:56:01,325 --> 00:56:04,027
Should we eat first and then get to work?

1109
00:56:04,027 --> 00:56:05,596
Be careful not to burn your hands.

1110
00:56:05,596 --> 00:56:07,831
- I cooled them in cold water.
- Did you?

1111
00:56:07,831 --> 00:56:10,228
Thank you. I appreciate it.

1112
00:56:12,369 --> 00:56:13,403
[Delicious]

1113
00:56:15,339 --> 00:56:16,406
Is it okay?

1114
00:56:16,406 --> 00:56:17,674
Is it not too hot?

1115
00:56:17,674 --> 00:56:19,714
- It tastes great.
- Really?

1116
00:56:20,477 --> 00:56:23,866
Ki Taek boiled these eggs.

1117
00:56:26,316 --> 00:56:29,052
[While They Play House,
Chef Cha Also Sets Out To Work]

1118
00:56:37,694 --> 00:56:40,864
[The King Of Baking Is Feeling Good Today]

1119
00:56:40,864 --> 00:56:42,599
[You Must Be Over 65 Years Old To Enter]

1120
00:56:42,599 --> 00:56:47,337
[Happily Humming]

1121
00:56:48,238 --> 00:56:49,306
[Startled]

1122
00:56:49,306 --> 00:56:50,607
Someone's humming.

1123
00:56:50,607 --> 00:56:52,609
Could it be Seung Won?

1124
00:56:52,609 --> 00:56:55,445
[Bingo]

1125
00:56:55,445 --> 00:56:57,814
Yes, he's here. It's Seung Won.

1126
00:56:57,814 --> 00:56:59,449
- Hello.
- Good morning.

1127
00:56:59,449 --> 00:57:00,751
- Would you like a coffee?
- Yes.

1128
00:57:00,751 --> 00:57:01,985
Hot or cold?

1129
00:57:01,985 --> 00:57:03,186
- Iced Americano.
- Okay.

1130
00:57:03,186 --> 00:57:04,354
- Seung Won.
- Yes?

1131
00:57:04,354 --> 00:57:08,892
I could hear humming from a mile away.

1132
00:57:08,892 --> 00:57:10,627
- That was me.
- I figured you were on your way.

1133
00:57:10,627 --> 00:57:12,747
[Locating Him Through Humming]
It's part of my routine.

1134
00:57:16,600 --> 00:57:18,001
Hello!

1135
00:57:18,769 --> 00:57:20,671
[Bonjour Bakery]
Hello.

1136
00:57:22,139 --> 00:57:27,344
[Thanks To The Great Weather,
The Morning Is Off To A Great Start]

1137
00:57:42,726 --> 00:57:45,996
[Thoroughly Cleaning Every Corner]

1138
00:57:47,164 --> 00:57:50,567
[Pulling Out All The Stops
For Today's Customers]

1139
00:57:51,435 --> 00:57:53,437
[Gochang's Mr. Handy]

1140
00:57:53,437 --> 00:57:55,572
[Mr. Handy Seon Ho]

1141
00:58:01,011 --> 00:58:03,647
[The Kitchen Team Also Happily Gets Ready]

1142
00:58:06,883 --> 00:58:07,884
What are you doing?

1143
00:58:08,885 --> 00:58:09,953
[Feeling Too Happy]
Is this right?

1144
00:58:09,953 --> 00:58:10,960
It's not a bad idea.

1145
00:58:10,960 --> 00:58:13,309
You need to get it right at the start.

1146
00:58:25,102 --> 00:58:28,372
[Checking Out His Reflection Like Chef Cha]

1147
00:58:28,372 --> 00:58:29,439
[And Blocking The Mirror]

1148
00:58:29,439 --> 00:58:30,807
Get out of the way.

1149
00:58:30,807 --> 00:58:33,977
I lowered it just a bit.

1150
00:58:33,977 --> 00:58:35,846
I pulled it down a little.

1151
00:58:35,846 --> 00:58:38,015
I nearly started the day with a scolding.

1152
00:58:38,015 --> 00:58:40,246
"Look here!"

1153
00:58:42,285 --> 00:58:45,122
[Ki Taek Fixes His Bandana In The Hall]

1154
00:58:46,023 --> 00:58:47,224
[He Wears It Stylishly Like Chef Cha]

1155
00:58:47,224 --> 00:58:49,559
[Laser-Focused Eyes]

1156
00:58:53,697 --> 00:58:55,766
How is it?

1157
00:58:55,766 --> 00:58:57,701
Is it looking good?

1158
00:58:57,701 --> 00:58:58,835
Do you like how you look?

1159
00:58:58,835 --> 00:59:01,705
Seeing you has made me lose confidence.

1160
00:59:01,705 --> 00:59:03,740
I thought I looked good in the mirror,

1161
00:59:03,740 --> 00:59:06,276
but I can't compete with you,
so I'll just get back to work.

1162
00:59:06,276 --> 00:59:08,645
- That was a good line.
- Thanks!

1163
00:59:08,645 --> 00:59:11,457
- Let's do this.
- Let's go.

1164
00:59:13,216 --> 00:59:16,486
[Bonjour Bakery]

1165
00:59:17,287 --> 00:59:20,690
[Seon Ho Folds Boxes
In A Corner Of The Hall]

1166
00:59:35,172 --> 00:59:36,348
Okay.

1167
00:59:37,707 --> 00:59:42,712
[He Folds Away Enthusiastically]

1168
00:59:43,947 --> 00:59:47,484
[And The Boxes Pile Up]

1169
01:00:00,697 --> 01:00:02,432
[Manager Hee Ae Has Arrived]

1170
01:00:02,432 --> 01:00:04,634
- Hi, Hee Ae.
- Good morning.

1171
01:00:05,836 --> 01:00:08,905
- Hi, Hee Ae.
- Good morning.

1172
01:00:08,905 --> 01:00:10,073
- Good morning.
- Did you come early?

1173
01:00:10,073 --> 01:00:11,308
Yes.

1174
01:00:11,308 --> 01:00:14,811
I figured we'd sell
a lot of baked goods today.

1175
01:00:14,811 --> 01:00:16,379
I came to fold more boxes.

1176
01:00:16,379 --> 01:00:18,915
[Great Work]

1177
01:00:19,583 --> 01:00:22,185
The market that opens
every five days is open today.

1178
01:00:22,185 --> 01:00:26,957
How about we go shopping
for today's lunch ingredients?

1179
01:00:26,957 --> 01:00:28,225
Five potatoes.

1180
01:00:28,225 --> 01:00:30,660
- Three onions.
- Got it.

1181
01:00:30,660 --> 01:00:32,529
Five carrots.

1182
01:00:32,529 --> 01:00:34,201
Sirloin for the curry.

1183
01:00:34,201 --> 01:00:36,266
We're having curry today?

1184
01:00:36,266 --> 01:00:39,169
- And curry powder.
- Otoki?

1185
01:00:39,169 --> 01:00:41,275
Two spicy packets.

1186
01:00:41,275 --> 01:00:42,868
If they have Vermont Curry,

1187
01:00:42,868 --> 01:00:44,961
- get two of those.
- Two Vermont Curries.

1188
01:00:44,961 --> 01:00:48,211
If not, just get two mild-flavor packets.

1189
01:00:48,211 --> 01:00:50,213
Sure, I like grocery shopping.

1190
01:00:50,213 --> 01:00:51,830
- Are you okay with going?
- Yes.

1191
01:00:52,682 --> 01:00:55,371
- Should we get going?
- Yes.

1192
01:01:01,310 --> 01:01:05,601
[Setting Off To Buy Ingredients For Lunch]

1193
01:01:05,601 --> 01:01:07,864
I know every actor is different.

1194
01:01:07,864 --> 01:01:13,203
Some use really tough methods
to get into character.

1195
01:01:13,203 --> 01:01:15,305
Some just have fun and enjoy the process,

1196
01:01:15,305 --> 01:01:18,742
- which can be very effective too.
- Yes.

1197
01:01:18,742 --> 01:01:20,510
- I've thought a lot
- Yes?

1198
01:01:20,510 --> 01:01:23,980
About which approach is better.

1199
01:01:23,980 --> 01:01:26,583
I used to be the former.

1200
01:01:26,583 --> 01:01:29,920
I would cut myself off from people
once I started filming.

1201
01:01:29,920 --> 01:01:32,322
[She Went To Great Lengths]
I used to feel guilty.

1202
01:01:32,322 --> 01:01:33,490
- But now...
- Yes?

1203
01:01:33,490 --> 01:01:35,225
I take my time and really enjoy myself.

1204
01:01:35,225 --> 01:01:37,427
Do you? But I think...

1205
01:01:37,427 --> 01:01:39,923
I think that's necessary.

1206
01:01:39,923 --> 01:01:42,332
- Even in the middle of a project,
- Yes.

1207
01:01:42,332 --> 01:01:43,533
You need to come up for air.

1208
01:01:43,533 --> 01:01:48,538
Sometimes you get so immersed
that you take a different path.

1209
01:01:48,538 --> 01:01:52,409
The director and other actors go one way,

1210
01:01:52,409 --> 01:01:53,843
and I veer off on my own

1211
01:01:53,843 --> 01:01:56,613
because I'm only focused on my character.

1212
01:01:56,613 --> 01:01:58,882
I don't know what the right answer is,

1213
01:01:58,882 --> 01:02:01,218
but compared to how I was before,

1214
01:02:01,218 --> 01:02:03,086
- I'm a lot more...
- You take it easier?

1215
01:02:03,086 --> 01:02:04,973
I've turned into a slacker.

1216
01:02:06,360 --> 01:02:08,892
- Really?
- But I don't think it's so bad.

1217
01:02:08,892 --> 01:02:12,295
- For really emotional scenes,
- Yes?

1218
01:02:12,295 --> 01:02:14,764
If the floor directors come up to me

1219
01:02:14,764 --> 01:02:18,969
while I'm focusing on getting into character,

1220
01:02:18,969 --> 01:02:21,052
- if they say, "Whenever you're ready..."
- Right?

1221
01:02:22,906 --> 01:02:25,976
My emotions just dry up.

1222
01:02:25,976 --> 01:02:28,778
I hate this phrase the most.

1223
01:02:28,778 --> 01:02:31,314
"Quiet!

1224
01:02:31,314 --> 01:02:33,450
Kim Hee Ae's getting into character,
so everyone be quiet!

1225
01:02:33,450 --> 01:02:35,685
Don't interrupt her
while she's getting focused.

1226
01:02:35,685 --> 01:02:37,157
This is a really important scene."

1227
01:02:37,157 --> 01:02:39,956
- "Ready? We're all set."
- Why do they do that?

1228
01:02:39,956 --> 01:02:43,693
"Whenever you're ready,
give us a sign, and we'll get rolling.

1229
01:02:43,693 --> 01:02:46,129
Get the cameras rolling.

1230
01:02:46,129 --> 01:02:48,198
Tell us when you're ready."

1231
01:02:48,198 --> 01:02:50,006
- When they do that...
- Say no more.

1232
01:02:50,006 --> 01:02:52,068
I really want to go home.

1233
01:02:52,068 --> 01:02:55,905
I would rather they just film us
while we're rehearsing

1234
01:02:55,905 --> 01:02:57,474
- so it feels natural.
- Exactly.

1235
01:02:57,474 --> 01:02:59,609
Then we can slip into character easily.

1236
01:02:59,609 --> 01:03:02,979
But if they shout,
"Focus! Quiet. Nobody move..."

1237
01:03:02,979 --> 01:03:04,080
It's so true.

1238
01:03:04,080 --> 01:03:05,582
[While Talking About The Filming Process]

1239
01:03:05,582 --> 01:03:07,951
[They Arrive At Gochang Traditional Market]

1240
01:03:10,287 --> 01:03:14,991
[It Started As The Town Market
Of Gochang In The Joseon Era]

1241
01:03:15,959 --> 01:03:19,896
[It Opens Every Five Days,
On Days Ending In 3 Or 8]

1242
01:03:25,568 --> 01:03:29,673
[The Local Produce Is Collected Here]

1243
01:03:30,840 --> 01:03:34,744
[As Well As Various Light Snacks]

1244
01:03:35,712 --> 01:03:40,483
[A Traditional Market That's Stood
Alongside The Community For Generations]

1245
01:03:40,483 --> 01:03:42,185
[Gochang Traditional Market]

1246
01:03:42,719 --> 01:03:46,589
- It's a huge market.
- You're right.

1247
01:03:46,589 --> 01:03:49,092
[Hee Ae And Seon Ho]

1248
01:03:49,092 --> 01:03:50,927
But if we want to buy curry powder-

1249
01:03:50,927 --> 01:03:54,164
Hee Ae, they sell syrup-filled pancakes.

1250
01:03:54,164 --> 01:03:55,265
- Pancakes?
- Fish cakes as well.

1251
01:03:55,265 --> 01:03:56,499
Let's first get what we need.

1252
01:03:56,499 --> 01:03:58,568
Oh, right.

1253
01:03:58,568 --> 01:04:01,004
We have to try the corn on the cob.

1254
01:04:01,004 --> 01:04:04,207
Hee Ae, in a market like this,
you need to snack while shopping.

1255
01:04:04,207 --> 01:04:05,975
Let's just get one.

1256
01:04:05,975 --> 01:04:07,210
Just one snack.

1257
01:04:07,210 --> 01:04:08,778
We need to hurry back.

1258
01:04:08,778 --> 01:04:10,686
- It's okay.
- There's a line.

1259
01:04:10,686 --> 01:04:13,083
[Hee Ae Is Worried
About Opening Preparations]

1260
01:04:13,083 --> 01:04:15,218
Should we get the corn or the pancakes?

1261
01:04:15,218 --> 01:04:16,553
How about one pancake each?

1262
01:04:16,553 --> 01:04:17,721
- One each?
- Yes.

1263
01:04:17,721 --> 01:04:20,290
- However you like.
- Okay.

1264
01:04:20,290 --> 01:04:24,160
Can we get it in a cup to eat
while walking around the market?

1265
01:04:28,531 --> 01:04:29,933
Oh, my.

1266
01:04:29,933 --> 01:04:32,168
He's frying rice flour donuts.

1267
01:04:32,168 --> 01:04:33,570
Those are so tasty.

1268
01:04:33,570 --> 01:04:35,372
[It Looks So Tasty]

1269
01:04:36,573 --> 01:04:40,377
[Rice Flour Donuts Are Being Fried
Next To The Pancakes]

1270
01:04:42,879 --> 01:04:45,701
- Should we buy some?
- The donuts?

1271
01:04:49,052 --> 01:04:52,822
[I Give Up]
Go on, then.

1272
01:04:53,456 --> 01:04:55,024
- Thank you.
- It's hot.

1273
01:04:55,024 --> 01:04:57,594
- Thank you.
- Wrap up 5,000 won worth.

1274
01:05:11,674 --> 01:05:13,243
- Here you go.
- Thank you. I hope you prosper.

1275
01:05:13,243 --> 01:05:15,044
- Thank you.
- Goodbye.

1276
01:05:15,044 --> 01:05:17,046
- Thank you.
- Let's go, Hee Ae.

1277
01:05:18,181 --> 01:05:21,851
[Pancake Stall]
I heard this is what you need to do.

1278
01:05:21,851 --> 01:05:23,820
[Time To Buy The Ingredients]
when you come to a market like this.

1279
01:05:23,820 --> 01:05:26,055
You need to have a snack in hand
while you browse.

1280
01:05:26,055 --> 01:05:27,647
That's true.

1281
01:05:28,792 --> 01:05:31,061
- There's so much sweetcorn.
- And fish cake bars.

1282
01:05:33,563 --> 01:05:34,825
Duck eggs.

1283
01:05:36,132 --> 01:05:37,801
- Hello.
- Hello.

1284
01:05:43,173 --> 01:05:45,642
That radish kimchi looks so good.

1285
01:05:46,242 --> 01:05:48,344
Hello, you're so young.

1286
01:05:50,146 --> 01:05:52,282
- These side dishes look so good.
- They are.

1287
01:05:52,282 --> 01:05:53,483
They look like it.

1288
01:05:53,483 --> 01:05:54,751
[You Can't Just Pass By]

1289
01:05:54,751 --> 01:05:56,319
Can I try a sample?

1290
01:05:56,319 --> 01:05:57,720
You can use those toothpicks.

1291
01:05:57,720 --> 01:05:59,472
Thank you.

1292
01:06:00,356 --> 01:06:02,826
[Salted Oysters]

1293
01:06:08,865 --> 01:06:10,409
It's so fresh.

1294
01:06:11,734 --> 01:06:13,002
Is it tasty?

1295
01:06:13,002 --> 01:06:14,571
Try it.

1296
01:06:21,110 --> 01:06:22,779
Do you like it?

1297
01:06:22,779 --> 01:06:24,117
- Let's get one of these.
- Yes.

1298
01:06:24,117 --> 01:06:26,316
The small one is 15,000 won,
and the large one is 20,000 won.

1299
01:06:26,316 --> 01:06:28,117
- We'll take the small one.
- The small size.

1300
01:06:28,117 --> 01:06:29,185
[Hee Ae Buys It For Seon Ho]

1301
01:06:29,185 --> 01:06:30,687
- Let's get some of this.
- That one?

1302
01:06:30,687 --> 01:06:31,888
- We'll take this as well.
- This one.

1303
01:06:31,888 --> 01:06:34,011
- Do you want 10,000 won worth?
- Yes.

1304
01:06:36,826 --> 01:06:38,027
Give them a lot.

1305
01:06:38,027 --> 01:06:39,762
Let's not buy anything else.

1306
01:06:39,762 --> 01:06:41,767
It all looks so tasty.

1307
01:06:44,901 --> 01:06:46,569
We've bought so much.

1308
01:06:46,569 --> 01:06:47,904
[Filled To The Brim]

1309
01:06:47,904 --> 01:06:49,138
- That's the stall.
- For what?

1310
01:06:49,138 --> 01:06:50,173
- We need to get-
- Potatoes?

1311
01:06:50,173 --> 01:06:52,942
[Finally Buying The Curry Ingredients]
We need potatoes, onions, and carrots.

1312
01:06:52,942 --> 01:06:56,346
Can we get five peeled carrots?

1313
01:06:56,346 --> 01:06:58,815
Yes, we'll take five of those.

1314
01:06:58,815 --> 01:06:59,883
[Lunch Grocery List]

1315
01:06:59,883 --> 01:07:01,117
- I'll take that.
- It's fine.

1316
01:07:01,117 --> 01:07:04,354
- Go ahead and pay first.
- We need 3 onions and 3 potatoes.

1317
01:07:04,354 --> 01:07:06,756
Sorry, we need five potatoes.

1318
01:07:06,756 --> 01:07:08,658
- These are newly harvested.
- Really?

1319
01:07:08,658 --> 01:07:09,959
[Buying Gochang's Locally Grown Produce]

1320
01:07:09,959 --> 01:07:10,860
Good job.

1321
01:07:10,860 --> 01:07:13,096
- Hello.
- Hi.

1322
01:07:13,096 --> 01:07:14,163
We need meat for curry.

1323
01:07:14,163 --> 01:07:17,100
- We need 800 grams of sirloin for curry.
- Okay.

1324
01:07:17,100 --> 01:07:20,169
Can you cut them into finger-sized pieces?

1325
01:07:20,169 --> 01:07:23,706
They must be the size of an index finger,
or else I'll get into serious trouble.

1326
01:07:23,706 --> 01:07:25,808
[Curry Sirloin Cut Into Index Finger-Sized Slices]

1327
01:07:26,576 --> 01:07:29,112
- The size of a finger.
- Okay, the size of an index finger.

1328
01:07:29,112 --> 01:07:31,032
[Sirloin Cuts Purchased
As Requested By Chef Cha]

1329
01:07:31,614 --> 01:07:33,449
Okay, let's go.

1330
01:07:34,450 --> 01:07:36,019
We bought everything on the list.

1331
01:07:36,019 --> 01:07:39,255
[We Got The Curry Powder
Now Let's Return To The Bakery]

1332
01:07:39,255 --> 01:07:40,323
Bring me...

1333
01:07:40,323 --> 01:07:41,691
[50 Minutes Before Opening]

1334
01:07:41,691 --> 01:07:43,593
Bring me the green barley

1335
01:07:43,593 --> 01:07:45,762
and sweet potato choux
we prepared earlier.

1336
01:07:48,197 --> 01:07:51,801
[Like A Fast-Spinning]

1337
01:07:51,801 --> 01:07:54,470
[Vertical Mixer]

1338
01:07:55,338 --> 01:07:57,941
[The Kitchen Team Is Operating]

1339
01:07:57,941 --> 01:08:02,111
[A Little Differently Than Usual]

1340
01:08:11,821 --> 01:08:13,990
- We need to arrange them like this.
- Okay.

1341
01:08:15,658 --> 01:08:18,861
[Why Is That?]

1342
01:08:20,897 --> 01:08:24,634
[To Take A Snapshot For His Core Memories]

1343
01:08:28,171 --> 01:08:30,440
I'll torch just two for now.
Thanks for the sugar.

1344
01:08:30,440 --> 01:08:31,480
[40 Minutes Until Opening]

1345
01:08:32,609 --> 01:08:35,645
[The Final Step To Caramelize The Top]

1346
01:08:57,934 --> 01:09:00,703
[Adding The Finishing Touches
Before The Customers Arrive]

1347
01:09:03,606 --> 01:09:05,341
- Move these carefully.
- Okay.

1348
01:09:05,341 --> 01:09:07,582
You need to be careful.

1349
01:09:11,347 --> 01:09:14,417
[Ki Taek Moves Them Onto A Plate]

1350
01:09:14,417 --> 01:09:16,352
Hey!

1351
01:09:16,352 --> 01:09:17,487
Hey!

1352
01:09:17,487 --> 01:09:20,189
[Flinching In Surprise]

1353
01:09:20,189 --> 01:09:21,724
Jeez, that was...

1354
01:09:21,724 --> 01:09:24,193
I nearly knocked the cake over.

1355
01:09:24,193 --> 01:09:27,063
He gave me such a scare.

1356
01:09:27,063 --> 01:09:28,231
Good thing I didn't.

1357
01:09:28,231 --> 01:09:29,399
[Cute Rascal]

1358
01:09:29,399 --> 01:09:31,000
Hold on. Let's go out together.

1359
01:09:31,000 --> 01:09:32,504
Okay.

1360
01:09:40,543 --> 01:09:45,548
[The Finished Desserts
Are Put On Display One By One]

1361
01:09:45,548 --> 01:09:47,450
Be gentle. Just use your left hand.

1362
01:09:47,450 --> 01:09:48,751
That one's fine. Leave it as it is.

1363
01:09:48,751 --> 01:09:50,053
- Okay.
- No.

1364
01:09:50,053 --> 01:09:51,721
- This one is good.
- The 11 o'clock and 4 o'clock direction.

1365
01:09:51,721 --> 01:09:52,622
- Yes.
- That's it.

1366
01:09:52,622 --> 01:09:54,257
Now they're positioned right.

1367
01:09:54,257 --> 01:09:55,858
[Setting Them At The Perfect Angle]

1368
01:09:55,858 --> 01:09:58,094
That's good.

1369
01:09:58,094 --> 01:10:00,697
They are all set now.

1370
01:10:01,631 --> 01:10:03,900
<i>When the display case is full like this,</i>

1371
01:10:03,900 --> 01:10:07,231
<i>since I know you made them,</i>

1372
01:10:07,231 --> 01:10:08,504
<i>I feel proud looking at them.</i>

1373
01:10:08,504 --> 01:10:10,506
<i>It's fun filling the display case.</i>

1374
01:10:12,942 --> 01:10:15,211
[Bonjour Chestnut And Pumpkin Babka]

1375
01:10:16,546 --> 01:10:19,615
[And 30 Minutes Before Opening]

1376
01:10:23,986 --> 01:10:26,155
[In Front Of The Bakery]

1377
01:10:26,155 --> 01:10:29,325
[Someone Stops In Their Tracks]

1378
01:10:52,915 --> 01:10:54,283
- It's...
- We also got radish kimchi.

1379
01:10:54,283 --> 01:10:57,420
It's made with winter radish,
and it's so sweet.

1380
01:10:57,420 --> 01:10:58,554
- Salted oysters.
- Yes.

1381
01:10:58,554 --> 01:11:00,523
- It looks so good.
- They taste so good.

1382
01:11:00,523 --> 01:11:03,392
- When did you get them?
- We tried a sample and had to get them.

1383
01:11:04,060 --> 01:11:05,628
[The Bakery Has A Visitor]

1384
01:11:05,628 --> 01:11:09,298
[Who Could It Be?]

1385
01:11:12,468 --> 01:11:14,637
[Bonjour Bakery]

1386
01:11:16,305 --> 01:11:19,776
[Bonjour Citron Madeleine]

1387
01:11:21,344 --> 01:11:24,480
[Filled With Fragrant Citron]

1388
01:11:26,015 --> 01:11:30,887
[Butter The Molds]

1389
01:11:30,887 --> 01:11:34,863
- Ki Taek, grab another brush and help.
- Okay.

1390
01:11:34,863 --> 01:11:36,183
[We're Busy So All Hands On Deck]

1391
01:11:36,859 --> 01:11:38,661
[The Molds Need To Be
Well-Buttered To The Edges]

1392
01:11:38,661 --> 01:11:40,730
[For The Madeleines
To Come Out In A Nice Shape]

1393
01:11:44,333 --> 01:11:46,135
- That's enough.
- Okay.

1394
01:11:46,135 --> 01:11:47,655
[The Molds Are Thoroughly Buttered Up]

1395
01:11:48,204 --> 01:11:49,872
[Gently Squeezing]

1396
01:11:53,843 --> 01:11:56,579
[Bonjour Citron Madeleine
Fill Each Mold With 40g Of Batter]

1397
01:12:00,316 --> 01:12:01,918
What do you think?

1398
01:12:01,918 --> 01:12:04,487
- That's the perfect amount.
- All right.

1399
01:12:04,487 --> 01:12:06,255
[You Need To Add The Right Amount]

1400
01:12:06,255 --> 01:12:08,424
[For A Pretty End Result]

1401
01:12:12,595 --> 01:12:14,463
[They're Perfect]
Yes.

1402
01:12:14,903 --> 01:12:17,773
[Human Scale]

1403
01:12:18,634 --> 01:12:20,269
[Suddenly Opens The Fridge]

1404
01:12:20,269 --> 01:12:21,170
What's up?

1405
01:12:21,170 --> 01:12:23,084
Just in case you need more.

1406
01:12:23,873 --> 01:12:26,876
[There Are 4 Left]

1407
01:12:27,777 --> 01:12:31,113
[But He's Running Short On Batter]

1408
01:12:31,113 --> 01:12:34,383
- This is the last of the batter.
- Seung Won.

1409
01:12:34,383 --> 01:12:36,118
We've sold a lot.

1410
01:12:36,118 --> 01:12:38,221
I think we can squeeze out one more.

1411
01:12:39,188 --> 01:12:40,188
[Squeeze]

1412
01:12:49,371 --> 01:12:50,533
- Wait a minute.
- Okay.

1413
01:12:50,533 --> 01:12:52,490
I think it's enough.

1414
01:12:53,369 --> 01:12:55,509
I'll try to squeeze it out.

1415
01:12:56,873 --> 01:12:58,140
[Grunting]

1416
01:13:01,010 --> 01:13:02,645
I think it'll work.

1417
01:13:02,645 --> 01:13:04,419
I think it's enough.

1418
01:13:08,684 --> 01:13:10,186
It's enough.

1419
01:13:10,186 --> 01:13:12,488
[The Final Mold Is Filled]

1420
01:13:12,488 --> 01:13:14,448
I got it. Hold on.

1421
01:13:16,759 --> 01:13:18,427
- I did it.
- It's perfect.

1422
01:13:18,427 --> 01:13:19,462
It's exactly 40 grams.

1423
01:13:19,462 --> 01:13:20,997
Okay, good.

1424
01:13:21,931 --> 01:13:23,666
- Get this in the freezer, please.
- Okay.

1425
01:13:23,666 --> 01:13:25,301
I'm on it.

1426
01:13:25,301 --> 01:13:27,303
- Fifteen minutes, right?
- Yes.

1427
01:13:27,303 --> 01:13:28,571
I'll set the timer here.

1428
01:13:28,571 --> 01:13:29,939
Okay.

1429
01:13:31,574 --> 01:13:32,642
Did you put it in?

1430
01:13:32,642 --> 01:13:34,359
Yes, it's in.

1431
01:13:36,712 --> 01:13:38,147
[The Batter Needs To Rest
In The Freezer For 15 Minutes]

1432
01:13:38,147 --> 01:13:40,706
It's in the freezer, right?

1433
01:13:43,786 --> 01:13:49,558
[The Cooled Batter
Is Then Baked In The Oven]

1434
01:13:51,260 --> 01:13:54,563
[After Baking For 13 Minutes At 170 Degrees]

1435
01:13:57,099 --> 01:14:00,803
[The Citron Madeleines Rise Up Beautifully]

1436
01:14:02,204 --> 01:14:04,173
[Citron Glaze]

1437
01:14:06,609 --> 01:14:10,780
[Once Fully Cooled,
They Are Coated With Citron Glazing]

1438
01:14:12,381 --> 01:14:13,449
Are you done?

1439
01:14:13,449 --> 01:14:15,262
- Yes, I'm done.
- Okay.

1440
01:14:18,621 --> 01:14:23,259
[Finally, The Glazed Madeleines
Are Baked Briefly To Dry]

1441
01:14:25,661 --> 01:14:27,541
[The Buttery, Fragrant Bonjour Citron Madeleine]
